var book = {
	"name": "2 Chronicles",
	"numChapters": 36,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11196A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11196A\"></sup>Solomon the son of David established himself in his kingdom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11196B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11196B\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God was with him and made him exceedingly great.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Solomon spoke to all Israel, to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11197C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11197C\"></sup>commanders of thousands and of hundreds, to the judges, and to all the leaders in all Israel, the heads of fathers' houses.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Solomon, and all the assembly with him, went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11198D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11198D\"></sup>the high place that was at Gibeon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11198E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11198E\"></sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11198F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11198F\"></sup>the tent of meeting of God, which Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made in the wilderness, was there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11199G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11199G\"></sup>(But David had brought up the ark of God from Kiriath-jearim to the place that David had prepared for it, for he had pitched a tent for it in Jerusalem.)",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11200H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11200H\"></sup>the bronze altar that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11200I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11200I\"></sup>Bezalel the son of Uri, son of Hur, had made, was there before the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And Solomon and the assembly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11200J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11200J\"></sup>sought it out.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Solomon went up there to the bronze altar before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which was at the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11201K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11201K\"></sup>and offered a thousand burnt offerings on it.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11202L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11202L\"></sup>In that night God appeared to Solomon, and said to him, “Ask what I shall give you.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Solomon said to God, “You have shown great and steadfast love to David my father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11203M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11203M\"></sup>and have made me king in his place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11204N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11204N\"></sup>let your word to David my father be now fulfilled, for you have made me king over a people as numerous <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11204O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11204O\"></sup>as the dust of the earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Give me now wisdom and knowledge to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11205P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11205P\"></sup>go out and come in before this people, for who can govern this people of yours, which is so great?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>God answered Solomon, “Because this was in your heart, and you have not asked for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11206Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11206Q\"></sup>possessions, wealth, honor, or the life of those who hate you, and have not even asked for long life, but have asked for wisdom and knowledge for yourself that you may govern my people over whom I have made you king,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>wisdom and knowledge are granted to you. I will also give you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11207R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11207R\"></sup>riches, possessions, and honor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11207S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11207S\"></sup>such as none of the kings had who were before you, and none after you shall have the like.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Solomon came from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11208T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11208T\"></sup>high place at Gibeon, from before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11208U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11208U\"></sup>the tent of meeting, to Jerusalem. And he reigned over Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11209V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11209V\"></sup>Solomon gathered together chariots and horsemen. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11209W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11209W\"></sup>He had 1,400 chariots and 12,000 horsemen, whom he stationed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11209X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11209X\"></sup>in the chariot cities and with the king in Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the king made silver and gold as common in Jerusalem as stone, and he made cedar as plentiful as the sycamore of the Shephelah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Solomon's import of horses was from Egypt and Kue, and the king's traders would buy them from Kue for a price.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They imported a chariot from Egypt for 600 shekels of silver, and a horse for 150. Likewise through them these were exported to all the kings of the Hittites and the kings of Syria."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11213A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11213A\"></sup>Now Solomon purposed to build a temple for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and a royal palace for himself.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11214B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11214B\"></sup>And Solomon assigned 70,000 men to bear burdens and 80,000 to quarry in the hill country, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11214C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11214C\"></sup>3,600 to oversee them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11215D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11215D\"></sup>And Solomon sent word to Hiram the king of Tyre: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11215E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11215E\"></sup>“As you dealt with David my father and sent him cedar to build himself a house to dwell in, so deal with me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Behold, I am about to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God and dedicate it to him for the burning of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11216F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11216F\"></sup>incense of sweet spices before him, and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11216G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11216G\"></sup>the regular arrangement of the showbread, and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11216H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11216H\"></sup>burnt offerings morning and evening, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11216I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11216I\"></sup>on the Sabbaths and the new moons and the appointed feasts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, as ordained forever for Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The house that I am to build will be great, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11217J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11217J\"></sup>for our God is greater than all gods.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11218K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11218K\"></sup>But who is able to build him a house, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11218L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11218L\"></sup>heaven, even highest heaven, cannot contain him? Who am I to build a house for him, except as a place to make offerings before him?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11219M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11219M\"></sup>send me a man skilled to work in gold, silver, bronze, and iron, and in purple, crimson, and blue fabrics, trained also in engraving, to be with the skilled workers who are with me in Judah and Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11219N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11219N\"></sup>whom David my father provided.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Send me also cedar, cypress, and algum timber from Lebanon, for I know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11220O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11220O\"></sup>your servants know how to cut timber in Lebanon. And my servants will be with your servants,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>to prepare timber for me in abundance, for the house I am to build will be great and wonderful.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11222P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11222P\"></sup>I will give for your servants, the woodsmen who cut timber, 20,000 cors of crushed wheat, 20,000 cors of barley, 20,000 baths of wine, and 20,000 baths of oil.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Hiram the king of Tyre answered in a letter that he sent to Solomon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11223Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11223Q\"></sup>“Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loves his people, he has made you king over them.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Hiram also said, “Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11224R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11224R\"></sup>who made heaven and earth, who has given King David a wise son, who has discretion and understanding, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11224S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11224S\"></sup>who will build a temple for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and a royal palace for himself.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Now I have sent a skilled man, who has understanding, Huram-abi,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11226T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11226T\"></sup>the son of a woman of the daughters of Dan, and his father was a man of Tyre. He is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11226U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11226U\"></sup>trained to work in gold, silver, bronze, iron, stone, and wood, and in purple, blue, and crimson fabrics and fine linen, and to do all sorts of engraving and execute any design that may be assigned him, with your craftsmen, the craftsmen of my lord, David your father.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now therefore the wheat and barley, oil and wine, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11227V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11227V\"></sup>of which my lord has spoken, let him send to his servants.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11228W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11228W\"></sup>And we will cut whatever timber you need from Lebanon and bring it to you in rafts by sea to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11228X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11228X\"></sup>Joppa, so that you may take it up to Jerusalem.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Solomon counted all the resident aliens who were in the land of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11229Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11229Y\"></sup>after the census of them that David his father had taken, and there were found 153,600.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11230Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11230Z\"></sup>Seventy thousand of them he assigned to bear burdens, 80,000 to quarry in the hill country, and 3,600 as overseers to make the people work."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11231A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11231A\"></sup>Then Solomon began to build the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11231B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11231B\"></sup>on Mount Moriah, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had appeared to David his father, at the place that David had appointed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11231C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11231C\"></sup>on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He began to build in the second month of the fourth year of his reign.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>These are Solomon's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11233D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11233D\"></sup>measurements for building the house of God: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11233E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11233E\"></sup>the length, in cubits of the old standard, was sixty cubits, and the breadth twenty cubits.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The vestibule in front of the nave of the house was twenty cubits long, equal to the width of the house, and its height was 120 cubits. He overlaid it on the inside with pure gold.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11235F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11235F\"></sup>The nave he lined with cypress and covered it with fine gold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11235G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11235G\"></sup>and made palms and chains on it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He adorned the house with settings of precious stones. The gold was gold of Parvaim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So he lined the house with gold—its beams, its thresholds, its walls, and its doors—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11237H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11237H\"></sup>and he carved cherubim on the walls.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11238I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11238I\"></sup>And he made the Most Holy Place. Its length, corresponding to the breadth of the house, was twenty cubits, and its breadth was twenty cubits. He overlaid it with 600 talents of fine gold.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The weight of gold for the nails was fifty shekels. And he overlaid <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11239J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11239J\"></sup>the upper chambers with gold.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11240K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11240K\"></sup>In the Most Holy Place he made two cherubim of wood and overlaid them with gold.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The wings of the cherubim together extended twenty cubits: one wing of the one, of five cubits, touched the wall of the house, and its other wing, of five cubits, touched the wing of the other cherub;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and of this cherub, one wing, of five cubits, touched the wall of the house, and the other wing, also of five cubits, was joined to the wing of the first cherub.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The wings of these cherubim extended twenty cubits. The cherubim stood on their feet, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11243L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11243L\"></sup>facing the nave.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11244M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11244M\"></sup>And he made the veil of blue and purple and crimson fabrics and fine linen, and he worked cherubim on it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11245N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11245N\"></sup>In front of the house he made two pillars thirty-five cubits high, with a capital of five cubits on the top of each.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He made chains like a necklace and put them on the tops of the pillars, and he made a hundred pomegranates and put them on the chains.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11247O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11247O\"></sup>He set up the pillars in front of the temple, one on the south, the other on the north; that on the south he called Jachin, and that on the north Boaz."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>He made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11248A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11248A\"></sup>an altar of bronze, twenty cubits long and twenty cubits wide and ten cubits high.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11249B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11249B\"></sup>Then he made the sea of cast metal. It was round, ten cubits from brim to brim, and five cubits high, and a line of thirty cubits measured its circumference.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Under it were figures of gourds, for ten cubits, compassing the sea all around. The gourds were in two rows, cast with it when it was cast.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>It stood on twelve oxen, three facing north, three facing west, three facing south, and three facing east. The sea was set on them, and all their rear parts were inward.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Its thickness was a handbreadth. And its brim was made like the brim of a cup, like the flower of a lily. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11252C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11252C\"></sup>It held 3,000 baths.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11253D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11253D\"></sup>He also made ten basins in which to wash, and set five on the south side, and five on the north side. In these they were to rinse off what was used for the burnt offering, and the sea was for the priests to wash in.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he made ten golden lampstands <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11254E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11254E\"></sup>as prescribed, and set them in the temple, five on the south side and five on the north.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11255F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11255F\"></sup>He also made ten tables and placed them in the temple, five on the south side and five on the north. And he made a hundred basins of gold.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11256G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11256G\"></sup>the court of the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11256H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11256H\"></sup>and the great court and doors for the court and overlaid their doors with bronze.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11257I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11257I\"></sup>And he set the sea at the southeast corner of the house.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11258J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11258J\"></sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11258K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11258K\"></sup>Hiram also made the pots, the shovels, and the basins. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11258L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11258L\"></sup>So Hiram finished the work that he did for King Solomon on the house of God:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the two pillars, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11259M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11259M\"></sup>the bowls, and the two capitals on the top of the pillars; and the two latticeworks to cover the two bowls of the capitals that were on the top of the pillars;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11260N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11260N\"></sup>and the 400 pomegranates for the two latticeworks, two rows of pomegranates for each latticework, to cover the two bowls of the capitals that were on the pillars.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11261O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11261O\"></sup>He made the stands also, and the basins on the stands,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the one sea, and the twelve oxen underneath it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The pots, the shovels, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11263P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11263P\"></sup>the forks, and all the equipment for these <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11263Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11263Q\"></sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11263R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11263R\"></sup>Huram-abi made of burnished bronze for King Solomon for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In the plain of the Jordan the king cast them, in the clay ground between Succoth and Zeredah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11265S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11265S\"></sup>Solomon made all these things in great quantities, for the weight of the bronze was not sought.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Solomon made all the vessels that were in the house of God: the golden altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11266T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11266T\"></sup>the tables for the bread of the Presence,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the lampstands and their lamps of pure gold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11267U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11267U\"></sup>to burn before the inner sanctuary, as prescribed;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>the flowers, the lamps, and the tongs, of purest gold;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>the snuffers, basins, dishes for incense, and fire pans, of pure gold, and the sockets of the temple, for the inner doors to the Most Holy Place and for the doors of the nave of the temple were of gold."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11270A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11270A\"></sup>Thus all the work that Solomon did for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was finished. And Solomon brought in the things that David his father had dedicated, and stored the silver, the gold, and all the vessels in the treasuries of the house of God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads of the tribes, the leaders of the fathers' houses of the people of Israel, in Jerusalem, to bring up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11271B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11271B\"></sup>the city of David, which is Zion.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And all the men of Israel assembled before the king at the feast that is in the seventh month.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And all the elders of Israel came, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11273C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11273C\"></sup>and the Levites took up the ark.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And they brought up the ark, the tent of meeting, and all the holy vessels that were in the tent; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11274D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11274D\"></sup>the Levitical priests brought them up.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And King Solomon and all the congregation of Israel, who had assembled before him, were before the ark, sacrificing so many sheep and oxen that they could not be counted or numbered.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the priests brought the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to its place, in the inner sanctuary of the house, in the Most Holy Place, underneath the wings of the cherubim.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The cherubim spread out their wings over the place of the ark, so that the cherubim made a covering above the ark and its poles.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the poles were so long that the ends of the poles were seen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11278E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11278E\"></sup>from the Holy Place before the inner sanctuary, but they could not be seen from outside. And they are there to this day.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>There was nothing in the ark except the two tablets <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11279F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11279F\"></sup>that Moses put there at Horeb, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with the people of Israel, when they came out of Egypt.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And when the priests came out of the Holy Place (for all the priests who were present had consecrated themselves, without regard to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11280G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11280G\"></sup>their divisions,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and all the Levitical <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11281H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11281H\"></sup>singers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11281I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11281I\"></sup>Asaph, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11281J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11281J\"></sup>Heman, and Jeduthun, their sons and kinsmen, arrayed in fine linen, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11281K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11281K\"></sup>cymbals, harps, and lyres, stood east of the altar with 120 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11281L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11281L\"></sup>priests who were trumpeters;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and it was the duty of the trumpeters and singers to make themselves heard in unison in praise and thanksgiving to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>), and when the song was raised, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11282M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11282M\"></sup>with trumpets and cymbals and other musical instruments, in praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11282N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11282N\"></sup>“For he is good,for his steadfast love endures forever,”the house, the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, was filled with a cloud,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>so that the priests could not stand to minister because of the cloud, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11283O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11283O\"></sup>for the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the house of God."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11284A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11284A\"></sup>Then Solomon said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said that he would dwell in thick darkness.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But I have built you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11285B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11285B\"></sup>an exalted house, a place for you to dwell in forever.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king turned around and blessed all the assembly of Israel, while all the assembly of Israel stood.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he said, “Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who with his hand has fulfilled what he promised with his mouth to David my father, saying,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘Since the day that I brought my people out of the land of Egypt, I chose no city out of all the tribes of Israel in which to build a house, that my name might be there, and I chose no man as prince over my people Israel;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11289C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11289C\"></sup>but I have chosen Jerusalem that my name may be there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11289D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11289D\"></sup>and I have chosen David to be over my people Israel.’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11290E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11290E\"></sup>Now it was in the heart of David my father to build a house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to David my father, ‘Whereas <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11291F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11291F\"></sup>it was in your heart to build a house for my name, you did well that it was in your heart.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Nevertheless, it is not you who shall build the house, but your son who shall be born to you shall build the house for my name.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has fulfilled his promise that he made. For I have risen in the place of David my father and sit on the throne of Israel, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised, and I have built the house for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And there I have set the ark, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11294G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11294G\"></sup>in which is the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he made with the people of Israel.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Solomon stood before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the presence of all the assembly of Israel and spread out his hands.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11296H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11296H\"></sup>Solomon had made a bronze platform five cubits long, five cubits wide, and three cubits high, and had set it in the court, and he stood on it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11296I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11296I\"></sup>Then he knelt on his knees in the presence of all the assembly of Israel, and spread out his hands toward heaven,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11297J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11297J\"></sup>there is no God like you, in heaven or on earth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11297K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11297K\"></sup>keeping covenant and showing steadfast love to your servants who walk before you with all their heart,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11298L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11298L\"></sup>who have kept with your servant David my father what you declared to him. You spoke with your mouth, and with your hand have fulfilled it this day.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now therefore, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel, keep for your servant David my father what you have promised him, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11299M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11299M\"></sup>‘You shall not lack a man to sit before me on the throne of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11299N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11299N\"></sup>if only your sons pay close attention to their way, to walk in my law as you have walked before me.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now therefore, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel, let your word be confirmed, which you have spoken to your servant David.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“But will God indeed dwell with man on the earth? Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11301O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11301O\"></sup>heaven and the highest heaven cannot contain you, how much less this house that I have built!",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Yet have regard to the prayer of your servant and to his plea, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, listening to the cry and to the prayer that your servant prays before you,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11303P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11303P\"></sup>that your eyes may be open day and night toward this house, the place where you have promised to set your name, that you may listen to the prayer that your servant offers toward this place.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And listen to the pleas of your servant and of your people Israel, when they pray toward this place. And listen from heaven your dwelling place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11304Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11304Q\"></sup>and when you hear, forgive.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“If a man sins against his neighbor and is made to take an oath and comes and swears his oath before your altar in this house,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>then hear from heaven and act and judge your servants, repaying the guilty by bringing his conduct on his own head, and vindicating the righteous by rewarding him according to his righteousness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“If your people Israel are defeated before the enemy because they have sinned against you, and they turn again and acknowledge your name and pray and plead with you in this house,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11308R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11308R\"></sup>then hear from heaven and forgive the sin of your people Israel and bring them again to the land that you gave to them and to their fathers.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11309S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11309S\"></sup>“When heaven is shut up and there is no rain because they have sinned against you, if they pray toward this place and acknowledge your name and turn from their sin, when you afflict them,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11310T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11310T\"></sup>then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your servants, your people Israel, when you teach them the good way in which they should walk, and grant rain upon your land, which you have given to your people as an inheritance.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11311U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11311U\"></sup>“If there is famine in the land, if there is pestilence or blight or mildew or locust or caterpillar, if their enemies besiege them in the land at their gates, whatever plague, whatever sickness there is,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>whatever prayer, whatever plea is made by any man or by all your people Israel, each knowing his own affliction and his own sorrow and stretching out his hands toward this house,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11313V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11313V\"></sup>then hear from heaven your dwelling place and forgive and render to each whose heart you know, according to all his ways, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11313W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11313W\"></sup>for you, you only, know the hearts of the children of mankind,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>that they may fear you and walk in your ways all the days that they live in the land that you gave to our fathers.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Likewise, when a foreigner, who is not of your people Israel, comes from a far country for the sake of your great name and your mighty hand and your outstretched arm, when he comes and prays toward this house,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>hear from heaven your dwelling place and do according to all for which the foreigner calls to you, in order that all the peoples of the earth may know your name and fear you, as do your people Israel, and that they may know that this house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11316X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11316X\"></sup>that I have built is called by your name.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“If your people go out to battle against their enemies, by whatever way you shall send them, and they pray to you toward this city that you have chosen and the house that I have built for your name,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>then hear from heaven their prayer and their plea, and maintain their cause.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“If they sin against you—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11319Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11319Y\"></sup>for there is no one who does not sin—and you are angry with them and give them to an enemy, so that they are carried away captive to a land far or near,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>yet if they turn their heart in the land to which they have been carried captive, and repent and plead with you in the land of their captivity, saying, ‘We have sinned and have acted perversely and wickedly,’",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>if they repent with all their heart and with all their soul in the land of their captivity to which they were carried captive, and pray toward their land, which you gave to their fathers, the city that you have chosen and the house that I have built for your name,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>then hear from heaven your dwelling place their prayer and their pleas, and maintain their cause and forgive your people who have sinned against you.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Now, O my God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11323Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11323Z\"></sup>let your eyes be open <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11323AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11323AA\"></sup>and your ears attentive to the prayer of this place.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“And now arise, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, and go to your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11324AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11324AB\"></sup>resting place,you and the ark of your might.Let your priests, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11324AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11324AC\"></sup>clothed with salvation,and let your saints <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11324AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11324AD\"></sup>rejoice in your goodness.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11325AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11325AE\"></sup>do not turn away the face of your anointed one!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11325AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11325AF\"></sup>Remember your steadfast love for David your servant.”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11326A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11326A\"></sup>As soon as Solomon finished his prayer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11326B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11326B\"></sup>fire came down from heaven and consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11326C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11326C\"></sup>and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the temple.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the priests could not enter the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s house.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When all the people of Israel saw the fire come down and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the temple, they bowed down with their faces to the ground on the pavement and worshiped and gave thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “For he is good, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11328D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11328D\"></sup>for his steadfast love endures forever.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11329E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11329E\"></sup>Then the king and all the people offered sacrifice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>King Solomon offered as a sacrifice 22,000 oxen and 120,000 sheep. So the king and all the people dedicated the house of God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The priests stood at their posts; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11331F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11331F\"></sup>the Levites also, with the instruments for music to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that King David had made for giving thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11331G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11331G\"></sup>for his steadfast love endures forever—whenever David offered praises by their ministry; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11331H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11331H\"></sup>opposite them the priests sounded trumpets, and all Israel stood.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11332I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11332I\"></sup>And Solomon consecrated the middle of the court that was before the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for there he offered the burnt offering and the fat of the peace offerings, because the bronze altar Solomon had made could not hold the burnt offering and the grain offering and the fat.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>At that time Solomon held the feast for seven days, and all Israel with him, a very great assembly, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11333J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11333J\"></sup>Lebo-hamath to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11333K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11333K\"></sup>Brook of Egypt.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And on the eighth day they held a solemn assembly, for they had kept the dedication of the altar seven days and the feast seven days.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>On the twenty-third day of the seventh month he sent the people away to their homes, joyful and glad of heart for the prosperity that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had granted to David and to Solomon and to Israel his people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11336L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11336L\"></sup>Thus Solomon finished the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king's house. All that Solomon had planned to do in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in his own house he successfully accomplished.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Solomon in the night and said to him: “I have heard your prayer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11337M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11337M\"></sup>and have chosen this place for myself as a house of sacrifice.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11338N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11338N\"></sup>When I shut up the heavens so that there is no rain, or command the locust to devour the land, or send pestilence among my people,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>if my people who are called by my name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11339O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11339O\"></sup>humble themselves, and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven and will forgive their sin and heal their land.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11340P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11340P\"></sup>Now my eyes will be open and my ears attentive to the prayer that is made in this place.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11341Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11341Q\"></sup>For now I have chosen and consecrated this house that my name may be there forever. My eyes and my heart will be there for all time.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And as for you, if you will walk before me as David your father walked, doing according to all that I have commanded you and keeping my statutes and my rules,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>then I will establish your royal throne, as I covenanted with David your father, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11343R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11343R\"></sup>‘You shall not lack a man to rule Israel.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11344S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11344S\"></sup>“But if you turn aside and forsake my statutes and my commandments that I have set before you, and go and serve other gods and worship them,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11345T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11345T\"></sup>then I will pluck you up from my land that I have given you, and this house that I have consecrated for my name, I will cast out of my sight, and I will make it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11345U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11345U\"></sup>a proverb and a byword among all peoples.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And at this house, which was exalted, everyone passing by will be astonished and say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11346V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11346V\"></sup>‘Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> done thus to this land and to this house?’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then they will say, ‘Because they abandoned the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers who brought them out of the land of Egypt, and laid hold on other gods and worshiped them and served them. Therefore he has brought all this disaster on them.’”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11348A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11348A\"></sup>At the end of twenty years, in which Solomon had built the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his own house,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Solomon rebuilt the cities that Hiram had given to him, and settled the people of Israel in them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Solomon went to Hamath-zobah and took it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He built Tadmor in the wilderness and all the store cities that he built in Hamath.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He also built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11352B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11352B\"></sup>Upper Beth-horon and Lower Beth-horon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11352C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11352C\"></sup>fortified cities <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11352D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11352D\"></sup>with walls, gates, and bars,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Baalath, and all the store cities that Solomon had and all the cities for his chariots and the cities for his horsemen, and whatever Solomon desired to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11354E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11354E\"></sup>All the people who were left of the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, who were not of Israel,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>from their descendants who were left after them in the land, whom the people of Israel had not destroyed—these Solomon drafted <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11355F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11355F\"></sup>as forced labor, and so they are to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But of the people of Israel Solomon made no slaves for his work; they were soldiers, and his officers, the commanders of his chariots, and his horsemen.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And these were the chief officers of King Solomon, 250, who exercised authority over the people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11358G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11358G\"></sup>Solomon brought Pharaoh's daughter up from the city of David to the house that he had built for her, for he said, “My wife shall not live in the house of David king of Israel, for the places to which the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has come are holy.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Solomon offered up burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11359H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11359H\"></sup>that he had built before the vestibule,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11360I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11360I\"></sup>as the duty of each day required, offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11360J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11360J\"></sup>according to the commandment of Moses for the Sabbaths, the new moons, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11360K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11360K\"></sup>three annual feasts—the Feast of Unleavened Bread, the Feast of Weeks, and the Feast of Booths.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>According to the ruling of David his father, he appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11361L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11361L\"></sup>the divisions of the priests for their service, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11361M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11361M\"></sup>and the Levites for their offices of praise and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11361N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11361N\"></sup>ministry before the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11361O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11361O\"></sup>as the duty of each day required, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11361P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11361P\"></sup>the gatekeepers in their divisions at each gate, for so David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11361Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11361Q\"></sup>the man of God had commanded.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And they did not turn aside from what the king had commanded the priests and Levites concerning any matter and concerning the treasuries.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Thus was accomplished all the work of Solomon from the day the foundation of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was laid until it was finished. So the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was completed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Solomon went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11364R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11364R\"></sup>Ezion-geber and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11364S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11364S\"></sup>Eloth on the shore of the sea, in the land of Edom.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Hiram sent to him by the hand of his servants ships and servants familiar with the sea, and they went to Ophir together with the servants of Solomon and brought from there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11365T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11365T\"></sup>450 talents of gold and brought it to King Solomon."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11366A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11366A\"></sup>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11366B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11366B\"></sup>the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon, she came to Jerusalem to test him with hard questions, having a very great retinue and camels bearing spices and very much gold and precious stones. And when she came to Solomon, she told him all that was on her mind.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Solomon answered all her questions. There was nothing hidden from Solomon that he could not explain to her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11368C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11368C\"></sup>the queen of Sheba had seen the wisdom of Solomon, the house that he had built,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the food of his table, the seating of his officials, and the attendance of his servants, and their clothing, his cupbearers, and their clothing, and his burnt offerings that he offered at the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, there was no more breath in her.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And she said to the king, “The report was true that I heard in my own land of your words and of your wisdom,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but I did not believe the reports until I came and my own eyes had seen it. And behold, half the greatness of your wisdom was not told me; you surpass the report that I heard.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Happy are your wives! Happy are these your servants, who continually stand before you and hear your wisdom!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has delighted in you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11373D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11373D\"></sup>and set you on his throne as king for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11373E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11373E\"></sup>Because your God loved Israel and would establish them forever, he has made you king over them, that you may execute justice and righteousness.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then she gave the king 120 talents of gold, and a very great quantity of spices, and precious stones. There were no spices such as those that the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Moreover, the servants of Hiram and the servants of Solomon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11375F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11375F\"></sup>who brought gold from Ophir, brought algum wood and precious stones.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the king made from the algum wood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11376G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11376G\"></sup>supports for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the king's house, lyres also and harps for the singers. There never was seen the like of them before in the land of Judah.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all that she desired, whatever she asked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11377H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11377H\"></sup>besides what she had brought to the king. So she turned and went back to her own land with her servants.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11378I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11378I\"></sup>Now the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was 666 talents of gold,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>besides that which the explorers and merchants brought. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11379J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11379J\"></sup>And all the kings of Arabia and the governors of the land brought gold and silver to Solomon.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>King Solomon made 200 large shields of beaten gold; 600 shekels of beaten gold went into each shield.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he made 300 shields of beaten gold; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11381K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11381K\"></sup>300 shekels of gold went into each shield; and the king put them in the House of the Forest of Lebanon.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The king also made a great ivory throne and overlaid it with pure gold.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The throne had six steps and a footstool of gold, which were attached to the throne, and on each side of the seat were armrests and two lions standing beside the armrests,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>while twelve lions stood there, one on each end of a step on the six steps. Nothing like it was ever made for any kingdom.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All King Solomon's drinking vessels were of gold, and all the vessels of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were of pure gold. Silver was not considered as anything in the days of Solomon.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For the king's ships went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11386L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11386L\"></sup>Tarshish with the servants of Hiram. Once every three years the ships of Tarshish used to come bringing gold, silver, ivory, apes, and peacocks.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Thus King Solomon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11387M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11387M\"></sup>excelled all the kings of the earth in riches and in wisdom.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And all the kings of the earth sought the presence of Solomon to hear his wisdom, which God had put into his mind.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Every one of them brought his present, articles of silver and of gold, garments, myrrh, spices, horses, and mules, so much year by year.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Solomon had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11390N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11390N\"></sup>4,000 stalls for horses and chariots, and 12,000 horsemen, whom he stationed in the chariot cities and with the king in Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11391O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11391O\"></sup>And he ruled over all the kings <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11391P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11391P\"></sup>from the Euphrates to the land of the Philistines and to the border of Egypt.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11392Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11392Q\"></sup>And the king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stone, and he made cedar as plentiful as the sycamore of the Shephelah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11393R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11393R\"></sup>And horses were imported for Solomon from Egypt and from all lands.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11394S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11394S\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11394T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11394T\"></sup>first to last, are they not written in the history of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11394U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11394U\"></sup>Nathan the prophet, and in the prophecy of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11394V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11394V\"></sup>Ahijah the Shilonite, and in the visions of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11394W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11394W\"></sup>Iddo <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11394X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11394X\"></sup>the seer concerning Jeroboam the son of Nebat?",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel forty years.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Solomon slept with his fathers and was buried in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11396Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11396Y\"></sup>the city of David his father, and Rehoboam his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11397A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11397A\"></sup>Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had come to Shechem to make him king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And as soon as Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard of it (for he was in Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11398B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11398B\"></sup>where he had fled from King Solomon), then Jeroboam returned from Egypt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they sent and called him. And Jeroboam and all Israel came and said to Rehoboam,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11400C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11400C\"></sup>“Your father made our yoke heavy. Now therefore lighten the hard service of your father and his heavy yoke on us, and we will serve you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to them, “Come to me again in three days.” So the people went away.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then King Rehoboam took counsel with the old men, who had stood before Solomon his father while he was yet alive, saying, “How do you advise me to answer this people?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And they said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11403D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11403D\"></sup>“If you will be good to this people and please them and speak good words to them, then they will be your servants forever.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But he abandoned the counsel that the old men gave him, and took counsel with the young men who had grown up with him and stood before him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he said to them, “What do you advise that we answer this people who have said to me, ‘Lighten the yoke that your father put on us’?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the young men who had grown up with him said to him, “Thus shall you speak to the people who said to you, ‘Your father made our yoke heavy, but you lighten it for us’; thus shall you say to them, ‘My little finger is thicker than my father's thighs.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And now, whereas my father laid on you a heavy yoke, I will add to your yoke. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as the king said, “Come to me again the third day.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the king answered them harshly; and forsaking the counsel of the old men,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>King Rehoboam spoke to them according to the counsel of the young men, saying, “My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to it. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the king did not listen to the people, for it was a turn of affairs brought about by God that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> might fulfill his word, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11411E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11411E\"></sup>which he spoke by Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And when all Israel saw that the king did not listen to them, the people answered the king, “What portion have we in David? We have no inheritance in the son of Jesse. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11412F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11412F\"></sup>Each of you to your tents, O Israel! Look now to your own house, David.” So all Israel went to their tents.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Rehoboam reigned over the people of Israel who lived in the cities of Judah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then King Rehoboam sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11414G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11414G\"></sup>Hadoram, who was taskmaster over the forced labor, and the people of Israel stoned him to death with stones. And King Rehoboam quickly mounted his chariot to flee to Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11416A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11416A\"></sup>When Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled the house of Judah and Benjamin, 180,000 chosen warriors, to fight against Israel, to restore the kingdom to Rehoboam.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11417B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11417B\"></sup>Shemaiah the man of God:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Say to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all Israel in Judah and Benjamin,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, You shall not go up or fight against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11419C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11419C\"></sup>your relatives. Return every man to his home, for this thing is from me.’” So they listened to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and returned and did not go against Jeroboam.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Rehoboam lived in Jerusalem, and he built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11420D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11420D\"></sup>cities for defense in Judah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He built Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Beth-zur, Soco, Adullam,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Gath, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11423E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11423E\"></sup>Mareshah, Ziph,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Adoraim, Lachish, Azekah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Zorah, Aijalon, and Hebron, fortified cities that are in Judah and in Benjamin.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He made the fortresses strong, and put commanders in them, and stores of food, oil, and wine.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he put shields and spears in all the cities and made them very strong. So he held Judah and Benjamin.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the priests and the Levites who were in all Israel presented themselves to him from all places where they lived.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For the Levites left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11429F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11429F\"></sup>their common lands and their holdings and came to Judah and Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11429G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11429G\"></sup>because Jeroboam and his sons cast them out from serving as priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and he appointed his own <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11430H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11430H\"></sup>priests for the high places and for the goat idols and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11430I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11430I\"></sup>the calves that he had made.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11431J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11431J\"></sup>And those who had set their hearts to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel came after them from all the tribes of Israel to Jerusalem to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11432K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11432K\"></sup>They strengthened the kingdom of Judah, and for three years they made Rehoboam the son of Solomon secure, for they walked for three years in the way of David and Solomon.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Rehoboam took as wife Mahalath the daughter of Jerimoth the son of David, and of Abihail the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11433L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11433L\"></sup>Eliab the son of Jesse,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and she bore him sons, Jeush, Shemariah, and Zaham.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After her he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11435M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11435M\"></sup>Maacah the daughter of Absalom, who bore him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11435N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11435N\"></sup>Abijah, Attai, Ziza, and Shelomith.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Rehoboam loved Maacah the daughter of Absalom above all his wives and concubines (he took eighteen wives and sixty concubines, and fathered twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters).",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11437O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11437O\"></sup>And Rehoboam appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11437P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11437P\"></sup>Abijah the son of Maacah as chief prince among his brothers, for he intended to make him king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he dealt wisely and distributed some of his sons through all the districts of Judah and Benjamin, in all the fortified cities, and he gave them abundant provisions and procured wives for them."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11439A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11439A\"></sup>When the rule of Rehoboam was established <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11439B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11439B\"></sup>and he was strong, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11439C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11439C\"></sup>he abandoned the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and all Israel with him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11440D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11440D\"></sup>In the fifth year of King Rehoboam, because they had been unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11440E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11440E\"></sup>Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>with 1,200 chariots and 60,000 horsemen. And the people were without number who came with him from Egypt—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11441F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11441F\"></sup>Libyans, Sukkiim, and Ethiopians.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11442G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11442G\"></sup>the fortified cities of Judah and came as far as Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11443H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11443H\"></sup>Shemaiah the prophet came to Rehoboam and to the princes of Judah, who had gathered at Jerusalem because of Shishak, and said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11443I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11443I\"></sup>‘You abandoned me, so I have abandoned you to the hand of Shishak.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the princes of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11444J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11444J\"></sup>Israel and the king humbled themselves and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11444K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11444K\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is righteous.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that they humbled themselves, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Shemaiah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11445L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11445L\"></sup>“They have humbled themselves. I will not destroy them, but I will grant them some deliverance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11445M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11445M\"></sup>and my wrath shall not be poured out on Jerusalem by the hand of Shishak.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Nevertheless, they shall be servants to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11446N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11446N\"></sup>that they may know my service and the service of the kingdoms of the countries.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11447O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11447O\"></sup>So Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem. He took away the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the treasures of the king's house. He took away everything. He also took away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11447P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11447P\"></sup>the shields of gold that Solomon had made,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and King Rehoboam made in their place shields of bronze and committed them to the hands of the officers of the guard, who kept the door of the king's house.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And as often as the king went into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the guard came and carried them and brought them back to the guardroom.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11450Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11450Q\"></sup>he humbled himself the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turned from him, so as not to make a complete destruction. Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11450R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11450R\"></sup>conditions were good in Judah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11451S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11451S\"></sup>So King Rehoboam grew strong in Jerusalem and reigned. Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel to put his name there. His mother's name was Naamah the Ammonite.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he did evil, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11452T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11452T\"></sup>for he did not set his heart to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11453U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11453U\"></sup>Now the acts of Rehoboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11453V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11453V\"></sup>from first to last, are they not written in the chronicles of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11453W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11453W\"></sup>Shemaiah the prophet and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11453X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11453X\"></sup>Iddo <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11453Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11453Y\"></sup>the seer? There were continual wars between Rehoboam and Jeroboam.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Rehoboam slept with his fathers and was buried in the city of David, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11454Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11454Z\"></sup>Abijah his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11455A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11455A\"></sup>In the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11455B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11455B\"></sup>Abijah began to reign over Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He reigned for three years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11456C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11456C\"></sup>Micaiah the daughter of Uriel of Gibeah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11456D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11456D\"></sup>Now there was war between Abijah and Jeroboam.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Abijah went out to battle, having an army of valiant men of war, 400,000 chosen men. And Jeroboam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11457E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11457E\"></sup>drew up his line of battle against him with 800,000 chosen mighty warriors.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Abijah stood up on Mount <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11458F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11458F\"></sup>Zemaraim that is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11458G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11458G\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim and said, “Hear me, O Jeroboam and all Israel!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ought you not to know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11459H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11459H\"></sup>gave the kingship over Israel forever to David and his sons by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11459I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11459I\"></sup>a covenant of salt?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Yet Jeroboam the son of Nebat, a servant of Solomon the son of David, rose up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11460J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11460J\"></sup>and rebelled against his lord,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and certain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11461K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11461K\"></sup>worthless scoundrels gathered about him and defied Rehoboam the son of Solomon, when Rehoboam was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11461L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11461L\"></sup>young and irresolute and could not withstand them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“And now you think to withstand the kingdom of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the hand of the sons of David, because you are a great multitude and have with you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11462M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11462M\"></sup>the golden calves that Jeroboam made you for gods.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11463N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11463N\"></sup>Have you not driven out the priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the sons of Aaron, and the Levites, and made priests for yourselves like the peoples of other lands? Whoever comes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11463O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11463O\"></sup>for ordination with a young bull or seven rams becomes a priest of what are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11463P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11463P\"></sup>not gods.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But as for us, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is our God, and we have not forsaken him. We have priests ministering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who are sons of Aaron, and Levites for their service.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11465Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11465Q\"></sup>every morning and every evening burnt offerings and incense of sweet spices, set out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11465R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11465R\"></sup>the showbread on the table of pure gold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11465S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11465S\"></sup>and care for the golden lampstand that its lamps may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11465T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11465T\"></sup>burn every evening. For we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11465U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11465U\"></sup>keep the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, but you have forsaken him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Behold, God is with us at our head, and his priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11466V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11466V\"></sup>with their battle trumpets to sound the call to battle against you. O sons of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11466W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11466W\"></sup>do not fight against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, for you cannot succeed.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jeroboam had sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11467X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11467X\"></sup>an ambush around to come upon them from behind. Thus his troops were in front of Judah, and the ambush was behind them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And when Judah looked, behold, the battle was in front of and behind them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11468Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11468Y\"></sup>And they cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11468Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11468Z\"></sup>blew the trumpets.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the men of Judah raised the battle shout. And when the men of Judah shouted, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11469AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11469AA\"></sup>God defeated Jeroboam and all Israel before Abijah and Judah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The men of Israel fled before Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11470AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11470AB\"></sup>and God gave them into their hand.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Abijah and his people struck them with great force, so there fell slain of Israel 500,000 chosen men.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Thus the men of Israel were subdued at that time, and the men of Judah prevailed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11472AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11472AC\"></sup>because they relied on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Abijah pursued Jeroboam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11473AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11473AD\"></sup>and took cities from him, Bethel with its villages and Jeshanah with its villages and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11473AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11473AE\"></sup>Ephron with its villages.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Jeroboam did not recover his power in the days of Abijah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11474AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11474AF\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck him down, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11474AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11474AG\"></sup>and he died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Abijah grew mighty. And he took fourteen wives and had twenty-two sons and sixteen daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The rest of the acts of Abijah, his ways and his sayings, are written in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11476AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11476AH\"></sup>story of the prophet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11476AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11476AI\"></sup>Iddo."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11477A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11477A\"></sup>Abijah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city of David. And Asa his son reigned in his place. In his days the land had rest for ten years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup> And Asa did what was good and right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He took away the foreign altars <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11479B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11479B\"></sup>and the high places and broke down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11479C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11479C\"></sup>the pillars and cut down the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11479D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11479D\"></sup>Asherim",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and commanded Judah to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, and to keep the law and the commandment.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He also took out of all the cities of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11481E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11481E\"></sup>the high places and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11481F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11481F\"></sup>incense altars. And the kingdom had rest under him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11482G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11482G\"></sup>fortified cities in Judah, for the land had rest. He had no war in those years, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11482H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11482H\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave him peace.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he said to Judah, “Let us build these cities and surround them with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11483I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11483I\"></sup>walls and towers, gates and bars. The land is still ours, because we have sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God. We have sought him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11483J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11483J\"></sup>and he has given us peace on every side.” So they built and prospered.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Asa had an army of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11484K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11484K\"></sup>300,000 from Judah, armed with large shields and spears, and 280,000 men from Benjamin that carried shields and drew bows. All these were mighty men of valor.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Zerah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11485L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11485L\"></sup>the Ethiopian came out against them with an army of a million men and 300 chariots, and came as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11485M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11485M\"></sup>Mareshah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Asa went out to meet him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11486N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11486N\"></sup>they drew up their lines of battle in the Valley of Zephathah at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11486O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11486O\"></sup>Mareshah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Asa <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11487P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11487P\"></sup>cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, there is none like you to help, between the mighty and the weak. Help us, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11487Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11487Q\"></sup>for we rely on you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11487R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11487R\"></sup>and in your name we have come against this multitude. O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you are our God; let not man prevail against you.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11488S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11488S\"></sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> defeated the Ethiopians before Asa and before Judah, and the Ethiopians fled.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Asa and the people who were with him pursued them as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11489T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11489T\"></sup>Gerar, and the Ethiopians fell until none remained alive, for they were broken before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his army. The men of Judah carried away very much spoil.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And they attacked all the cities around <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11490U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11490U\"></sup>Gerar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11490V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11490V\"></sup>for the fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was upon them. They plundered all the cities, for there was much plunder in them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And they struck down the tents of those who had livestock and carried away sheep in abundance and camels. Then they returned to Jerusalem."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11492A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11492A\"></sup>The Spirit of God came upon Azariah the son of Oded,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and he went out to meet Asa and said to him, “Hear me, Asa, and all Judah and Benjamin: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11493B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11493B\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you while you are with him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11493C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11493C\"></sup>If you seek him, he will be found by you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11493D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11493D\"></sup>but if you forsake him, he will forsake you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11494E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11494E\"></sup>For a long time Israel was without the true God, and without a teaching priest and without law,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11495F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11495F\"></sup>but when in their distress they turned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, and sought him, he was found by them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In those times there was no peace <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11496G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11496G\"></sup>to him who went out or to him who came in, for great disturbances afflicted all the inhabitants of the lands.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They were broken in pieces. Nation was crushed by nation and city by city, for God troubled them with every sort of distress.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11498H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11498H\"></sup>But you, take courage! Do not let your hands be weak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11498I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11498I\"></sup>for your work shall be rewarded.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>As soon as Asa heard these words, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11499J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11499J\"></sup>the prophecy of Azariah the son of Oded, he took courage and put away the detestable idols from all the land of Judah and Benjamin and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11499K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11499K\"></sup>the cities that he had taken in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11499L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11499L\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, and he repaired the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11499M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11499M\"></sup>that was in front of the vestibule of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he gathered all Judah and Benjamin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11500N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11500N\"></sup>and those from Ephraim, Manasseh, and Simeon who were residing with them, for great numbers had deserted to him from Israel when they saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God was with him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They were gathered at Jerusalem in the third month of the fifteenth year of the reign of Asa.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They sacrificed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11502O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11502O\"></sup>from the spoil that they had brought 700 oxen and 7,000 sheep.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11503P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11503P\"></sup>And they entered into a covenant to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, with all their heart and with all their soul,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>but that whoever would not seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11504Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11504Q\"></sup>should be put to death, whether young or old, man or woman.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They swore an oath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with a loud voice and with shouting and with trumpets and with horns.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And all Judah rejoiced over the oath, for they had sworn with all their heart and had sought him with their whole desire, and he was found by them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11506R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11506R\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them rest all around.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11507S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11507S\"></sup>Even Maacah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11507T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11507T\"></sup>his mother, King Asa removed from being queen mother because she had made a detestable image <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11507U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11507U\"></sup>for Asherah. Asa cut down her image, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11507V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11507V\"></sup>crushed it, and burned it at the brook Kidron.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11508W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11508W\"></sup>But the high places were not taken out of Israel. Nevertheless, the heart of Asa was wholly true all his days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he brought into the house of God the sacred gifts of his father and his own sacred gifts, silver, and gold, and vessels.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And there was no more war until the thirty-fifth year of the reign of Asa."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11511A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11511A\"></sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11511B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11511B\"></sup>thirty-sixth year of the reign of Asa, Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah and built Ramah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11511C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11511C\"></sup>that he might permit no one to go out or come in to Asa king of Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Asa took silver and gold from the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king's house and sent them to Ben-hadad king of Syria, who lived in Damascus, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“There is a covenant between me and you, as there was between my father and your father. Behold, I am sending to you silver and gold. Go, break your covenant with Baasha king of Israel, that he may withdraw from me.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Ben-hadad listened to King Asa and sent the commanders of his armies against the cities of Israel, and they conquered Ijon, Dan, Abel-maim, and all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11514D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11514D\"></sup>store cities of Naphtali.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when Baasha heard of it, he stopped building Ramah and let his work cease.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then King Asa took all Judah, and they carried away the stones of Ramah and its timber, with which Baasha had been building, and with them he built Geba and Mizpah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11517E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11517E\"></sup>Hanani <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11517F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11517F\"></sup>the seer came to Asa king of Judah and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11517G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11517G\"></sup>“Because you relied on the king of Syria, and did not rely on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, the army of the king of Syria has escaped you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Were not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11518H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11518H\"></sup>the Ethiopians and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11518I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11518I\"></sup>the Libyans a huge army with very many chariots and horsemen? Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11518J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11518J\"></sup>because you relied on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he gave them into your hand.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11519K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11519K\"></sup>For the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> run to and fro throughout the whole earth, to give strong support to those <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11519L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11519L\"></sup>whose heart is blameless toward him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11519M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11519M\"></sup>You have done foolishly in this, for from now on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11519N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11519N\"></sup>you will have wars.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Asa was angry with the seer and put him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11520O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11520O\"></sup>in the stocks in prison, for he was in a rage with him because of this. And Asa inflicted cruelties upon some of the people at the same time.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11521P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11521P\"></sup>The acts of Asa, from first to last, are written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In the thirty-ninth year of his reign Asa was diseased in his feet, and his disease became severe. Yet even in his disease he did not seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but sought help from physicians.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Asa slept with his fathers, dying in the forty-first year of his reign.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They buried him in the tomb that he had cut for himself in the city of David. They laid him on a bier <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11524Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11524Q\"></sup>that had been filled with various kinds of spices prepared by the perfumer's art, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11524R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11524R\"></sup>and they made a very great fire in his honor."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place and strengthened himself against Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He placed forces in all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11526A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11526A\"></sup>fortified cities of Judah and set garrisons in the land of Judah, and in the cities of Ephraim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11526B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11526B\"></sup>that Asa his father had captured.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Jehoshaphat, because he walked in the earlier ways of his father David. He did not seek the Baals,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>but sought the God of his father and walked in his commandments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11528C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11528C\"></sup>and not according to the practices of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> established the kingdom in his hand. And all Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11529D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11529D\"></sup>brought tribute to Jehoshaphat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11529E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11529E\"></sup>and he had great riches and honor.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>His heart was courageous in the ways of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And furthermore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11530F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11530F\"></sup>he took the high places and the Asherim out of Judah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In the third year of his reign he sent his officials, Ben-hail, Obadiah, Zechariah, Nethanel, and Micaiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11531G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11531G\"></sup>to teach in the cities of Judah;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11532H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11532H\"></sup>and with them the Levites, Shemaiah, Nethaniah, Zebadiah, Asahel, Shemiramoth, Jehonathan, Adonijah, Tobijah, and Tobadonijah; and with these Levites, the priests Elishama and Jehoram.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11533I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11533I\"></sup>they taught in Judah, having the Book of the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with them. They went about through all the cities of Judah and taught among the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11534J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11534J\"></sup>And the fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fell upon all the kingdoms of the lands that were around Judah, and they made no war against Jehoshaphat.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Some of the Philistines <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11535K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11535K\"></sup>brought Jehoshaphat presents and silver for tribute, and the Arabians also brought him 7,700 rams and 7,700 goats.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Jehoshaphat grew steadily greater. He built in Judah fortresses and store cities,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and he had large supplies in the cities of Judah. He had soldiers, mighty men of valor, in Jerusalem.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>This was the muster of them by fathers' houses: Of Judah, the commanders of thousands: Adnah the commander, with 300,000 mighty men of valor;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and next to him Jehohanan the commander, with 280,000;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and next to him Amasiah the son of Zichri, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11540L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11540L\"></sup>a volunteer for the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with 200,000 mighty men of valor.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Of Benjamin: Eliada, a mighty man of valor, with 200,000 men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11541M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11541M\"></sup>armed with bow and shield;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and next to him Jehozabad with 180,000 armed for war.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These were in the service of the king, besides <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11543N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11543N\"></sup>those whom the king had placed in the fortified cities throughout all Judah."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now Jehoshaphat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11544A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11544A\"></sup>had great riches and honor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11544B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11544B\"></sup>and he made a marriage alliance with Ahab.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11545C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11545C\"></sup>After some years he went down to Ahab in Samaria. And Ahab killed an abundance of sheep and oxen for him and for the people who were with him, and induced him to go up against Ramoth-gilead.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Ahab king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, “Will you go with me to Ramoth-gilead?” He answered him, “I am as you are, my people as your people. We will be with you in the war.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, “Inquire first for the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, four hundred men, and said to them, “Shall we go to battle against Ramoth-gilead, or shall I refrain?” And they said, “Go up, for God will give it into the hand of the king.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Jehoshaphat said, “Is there not here another prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of whom we may inquire?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “There is yet one man by whom we may inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Micaiah the son of Imlah; but I hate him, for he never prophesies good concerning me, but always evil.” And Jehoshaphat said, “Let not the king say so.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the king of Israel summoned an officer and said, “Bring quickly Micaiah the son of Imlah.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah were sitting on their thrones, arrayed in their robes. And they were sitting at the threshing floor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11552D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11552D\"></sup>at the entrance of the gate of Samaria, and all the prophets were prophesying before them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made for himself horns of iron and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘With these you shall push the Syrians until they are destroyed.’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And all the prophets prophesied so and said, “Go up to Ramoth-gilead and triumph. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give it into the hand of the king.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the messenger who went to summon Micaiah said to him, “Behold, the words of the prophets with one accord are favorable to the king. Let your word be like the word of one of them, and speak favorably.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Micaiah said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11556E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11556E\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11556F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11556F\"></sup>what my God says, that I will speak.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And when he had come to the king, the king said to him, “Micaiah, shall we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall I refrain?” And he answered, “Go up and triumph; they will be given into your hand.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the king said to him, “How many times shall I make you swear that you speak to me nothing but the truth in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he said, “I saw all Israel scattered on the mountains, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11559G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11559G\"></sup>as sheep that have no shepherd. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘These have no master; let each return to his home in peace.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “Did I not tell you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Micaiah said, “Therefore hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11561H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11561H\"></sup>I saw the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sitting on his throne, and all the host of heaven standing on his right hand and on his left.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘Who will entice Ahab the king of Israel, that he may go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead?’ And one said one thing, and another said another.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then a spirit came forward and stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, ‘I will entice him.’ And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, ‘By what means?’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he said, ‘I will go out, and will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11564I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11564I\"></sup>a lying spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.’ And he said, ‘You are to entice him, and you shall succeed; go out and do so.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now therefore behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has put a lying spirit in the mouth of these your prophets. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has declared disaster concerning you.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11566J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11566J\"></sup>and struck Micaiah on the cheek and said, “Which way did the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> go from me to speak to you?”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Micaiah said, “Behold, you shall see on that day when you go into an inner chamber to hide yourself.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the king of Israel said, “Seize Micaiah and take him back to Amon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11568K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11568K\"></sup>the governor of the city and to Joash the king's son,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and say, ‘Thus says the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11569L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11569L\"></sup>Put this fellow in prison and feed him with meager rations of bread and water until I return in peace.’”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Micaiah said, “If you return in peace, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken by me.” And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11570M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11570M\"></sup>“Hear, all you peoples!”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to Ramoth-gilead.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “I will disguise myself and go into battle, but you wear your robes.” And the king of Israel disguised himself, and they went into battle.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now the king of Syria had commanded the captains of his chariots, “Fight with neither small nor great, but only with the king of Israel.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As soon as the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said, “It is the king of Israel.” So they turned to fight against him. And Jehoshaphat cried out, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helped him; God drew them away from him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For as soon as the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of Israel, they turned back from pursuing him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But a certain man drew his bow at random and struck the king of Israel between the scale armor and the breastplate. Therefore he said to the driver of his chariot, “Turn around and carry me out of the battle, for I am wounded.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And the battle continued that day, and the king of Israel was propped up in his chariot facing the Syrians until evening. Then at sunset he died."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Jehoshaphat the king of Judah returned in safety to his house in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11579A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11579A\"></sup>Jehu the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11579B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11579B\"></sup>Hanani <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11579C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11579C\"></sup>the seer went out to meet him and said to King Jehoshaphat, “Should you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11579D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11579D\"></sup>help the wicked and love those who hate the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>? Because of this, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11579E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11579E\"></sup>wrath has gone out against you from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11580F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11580F\"></sup>some good is found in you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11580G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11580G\"></sup>you destroyed the Asheroth out of the land, and have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11580H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11580H\"></sup>set your heart to seek God.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jehoshaphat lived at Jerusalem. And he went out again among the people, from Beersheba to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11581I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11581I\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, and brought them back to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11582J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11582J\"></sup>judges in the land in all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11582K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11582K\"></sup>the fortified cities of Judah, city by city,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and said to the judges, “Consider what you do, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11583L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11583L\"></sup>for you judge not for man but for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He is with you in giving judgment.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now then, let the fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be upon you. Be careful what you do, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11584M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11584M\"></sup>there is no injustice with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11584N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11584N\"></sup>or partiality or taking bribes.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Moreover, in Jerusalem Jehoshaphat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11585O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11585O\"></sup>appointed certain Levites and priests and heads of families of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11585P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11585P\"></sup>to give judgment for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to decide disputed cases. They had their seat at Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he charged them: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11586Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11586Q\"></sup>“Thus you shall do in the fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in faithfulness, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11586R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11586R\"></sup>and with your whole heart:",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11587S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11587S\"></sup>whenever a case comes to you from your brothers who live in their cities, concerning bloodshed, law or commandment, statutes or rules, then you shall warn them, that they may not incur guilt before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11587T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11587T\"></sup>wrath may not come upon you and your brothers. Thus you shall do, and you will not incur guilt.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And behold, Amariah the chief priest is over you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11588U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11588U\"></sup>in all matters of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and Zebadiah the son of Ishmael, the governor of the house of Judah, in all the king's matters, and the Levites will serve you as officers. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11588V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11588V\"></sup>Deal courageously, and may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with the upright!”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>After this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11589A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11589A\"></sup>the Moabites and Ammonites, and with them some of the Meunites, came against Jehoshaphat for battle.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Some men came and told Jehoshaphat, “A great multitude is coming against you from Edom, from beyond the sea; and, behold, they are in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11590B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11590B\"></sup>Hazazon-tamar” (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11590C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11590C\"></sup>Engedi).",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Jehoshaphat was afraid and set his face <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11591D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11591D\"></sup>to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11591E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11591E\"></sup>proclaimed a fast throughout all Judah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Judah assembled to seek help from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; from all the cities of Judah they came to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Jehoshaphat stood in the assembly of Judah and Jerusalem, in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, before the new court,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of our fathers, are you not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11594F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11594F\"></sup>God in heaven? You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11594G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11594G\"></sup>rule over all the kingdoms of the nations. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11594H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11594H\"></sup>In your hand are power and might, so that none is able to withstand you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Did you not, our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11595I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11595I\"></sup>drive out the inhabitants of this land before your people Israel, and give it forever to the descendants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11595J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11595J\"></sup>Abraham your friend?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And they have lived in it and have built for you in it a sanctuary for your name, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11597K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11597K\"></sup>‘If disaster comes upon us, the sword, judgment, or pestilence, or famine, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11597L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11597L\"></sup>we will stand before this house and before you—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11597M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11597M\"></sup>for your name is in this house—and cry out to you in our affliction, and you will hear and save.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And now behold, the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11598N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11598N\"></sup>Ammon and Moab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11598O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11598O\"></sup>Mount Seir, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11598P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11598P\"></sup>you would not let Israel invade when they came from the land of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11598Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11598Q\"></sup>and whom they avoided and did not destroy—",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>behold, they reward us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11599R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11599R\"></sup>by coming to drive us out of your possession, which you have given us to inherit.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>O our God, will you not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11600S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11600S\"></sup>execute judgment on them? For we are powerless against this great horde that is coming against us. We do not know what to do, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11600T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11600T\"></sup>our eyes are on you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Meanwhile all Judah stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with their little ones, their wives, and their children.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11602U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11602U\"></sup>the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came upon Jahaziel the son of Zechariah, son of Benaiah, son of Jeiel, son of Mattaniah, a Levite of the sons of Asaph, in the midst of the assembly.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he said, “Listen, all Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem and King Jehoshaphat: Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11603V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11603V\"></sup>‘Do not be afraid and do not be dismayed at this great horde, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11603W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11603W\"></sup>for the battle is not yours but God's.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Tomorrow go down against them. Behold, they will come up by the ascent of Ziz. You will find them at the end of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11604X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11604X\"></sup>the valley, east of the wilderness of Jeruel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11605Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11605Y\"></sup>You will not need to fight in this battle. Stand firm, hold your position, and see the salvation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on your behalf, O Judah and Jerusalem.’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11605Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11605Z\"></sup>Do not be afraid and do not be dismayed. Tomorrow go out against them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11605AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11605AA\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be with you.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Jehoshaphat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11606AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11606AB\"></sup>bowed his head with his face to the ground, and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem fell down before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, worshiping the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the Levites, of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11607AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11607AC\"></sup>Kohathites and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11607AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11607AD\"></sup>Korahites, stood up to praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, with a very loud voice.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And they rose early in the morning and went out into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11608AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11608AE\"></sup>the wilderness of Tekoa. And when they went out, Jehoshaphat stood and said, “Hear me, Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11608AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11608AF\"></sup>Believe in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and you will be established; believe his prophets, and you will succeed.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And when he had taken counsel with the people, he appointed those who were to sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and praise him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11609AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11609AG\"></sup>in holy attire, as they went before the army, and say,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11609AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11609AH\"></sup>“Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for his steadfast love endures forever.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And when they began to sing and praise, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11610AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11610AI\"></sup>an ambush against the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11610AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11610AJ\"></sup>Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir, who had come against Judah, so that they were routed.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For the men of Ammon and Moab rose against the inhabitants of Mount Seir, devoting them to destruction, and when they had made an end of the inhabitants of Seir, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11611AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11611AK\"></sup>they all helped to destroy one another.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Judah came to the watchtower of the wilderness, they looked toward the horde, and behold, there were dead bodies lying on the ground; none had escaped.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When Jehoshaphat and his people came to take their spoil, they found among them, in great numbers, goods, clothing, and precious things, which they took for themselves until they could carry no more. They were three days in taking the spoil, it was so much.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>On the fourth day they assembled in the Valley of Beracah, for there they blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Therefore the name of that place has been called the Valley of Beracah to this day.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then they returned, every man of Judah and Jerusalem, and Jehoshaphat at their head, returning to Jerusalem with joy, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11615AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11615AL\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made them rejoice over their enemies.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They came to Jerusalem with harps and lyres and trumpets, to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11617AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11617AM\"></sup>And the fear of God came on all the kingdoms of the countries when they heard that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had fought against the enemies of Israel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So the realm of Jehoshaphat was quiet, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11618AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11618AN\"></sup>for his God gave him rest all around.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11619AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11619AO\"></sup>Thus Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah. He was thirty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He walked in the way of Asa his father and did not turn aside from it, doing what was right in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11621AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11621AP\"></sup>The high places, however, were not taken away; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11621AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11621AQ\"></sup>the people had not yet set their hearts upon the God of their fathers.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, from first to last, are written in the chronicles of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11622AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11622AR\"></sup>Jehu the son of Hanani, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11622AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11622AS\"></sup>which are recorded in the Book of the Kings of Israel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11623AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11623AT\"></sup>After this Jehoshaphat king of Judah joined with Ahaziah king of Israel, who acted wickedly.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He joined him in building ships to go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11624AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11624AU\"></sup>Tarshish, and they built the ships in Ezion-geber.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then Eliezer the son of Dodavahu of Mareshah prophesied against Jehoshaphat, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11625AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11625AV\"></sup>“Because you have joined with Ahaziah, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will destroy what you have made.” And the ships were wrecked and were not able to go to Tarshish."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11626A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11626A\"></sup>Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David, and Jehoram his son reigned in his place.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He had brothers, the sons of Jehoshaphat: Azariah, Jehiel, Zechariah, Azariah, Michael, and Shephatiah; all these were the sons of Jehoshaphat king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11627B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11627B\"></sup>Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Their father gave them great gifts of silver, gold, and valuable possessions, together with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11628C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11628C\"></sup>fortified cities in Judah, but he gave the kingdom to Jehoram, because he was the firstborn.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When Jehoram had ascended the throne of his father and was established, he killed all his brothers with the sword, and also some of the princes of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11629D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11629D\"></sup>Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11630E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11630E\"></sup>Jehoram was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11630F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11630F\"></sup>thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11631G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11631G\"></sup>And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, as the house of Ahab had done, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11631H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11631H\"></sup>the daughter of Ahab was his wife. And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Yet the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not willing to destroy the house of David, because of the covenant that he had made with David, and since he had promised to give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11632I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11632I\"></sup>a lamp to him and to his sons forever.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In his days Edom revolted from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11633J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11633J\"></sup>rule of Judah and set up a king of their own.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Jehoram passed over with his commanders and all his chariots, and he rose by night and struck the Edomites who had surrounded him and his chariot commanders.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Edom revolted from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11635K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11635K\"></sup>the rule of Judah to this day. At that time Libnah also revolted from his rule, because he had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his fathers.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Moreover, he made high places in the hill country of Judah and led the inhabitants of Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11636L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11636L\"></sup>into whoredom and made Judah go astray.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And a letter came to him from Elijah the prophet, saying, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of David your father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11637M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11637M\"></sup>‘Because you have not walked in the ways of Jehoshaphat your father, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11637N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11637N\"></sup>in the ways of Asa king of Judah,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11638O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11638O\"></sup>but have walked in the way of the kings of Israel and have enticed Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11638P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11638P\"></sup>into whoredom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11638Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11638Q\"></sup>as the house of Ahab led Israel into whoredom, and also you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11638R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11638R\"></sup>have killed your brothers, of your father's house, who were better than you,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring a great plague on your people, your children, your wives, and all your possessions,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and you yourself will have a severe sickness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11640S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11640S\"></sup>with a disease of your bowels, until your bowels come out because of the disease, day by day.’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11641T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11641T\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stirred up against Jehoram the anger of the Philistines and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11641U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11641U\"></sup>the Arabians who are near the Ethiopians.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they came up against Judah and invaded it and carried away all the possessions they found that belonged to the king's house, and also his sons and his wives, so that no son was left to him except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11642V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11642V\"></sup>Jehoahaz, his youngest son.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And after all this the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11643W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11643W\"></sup>in his bowels with an incurable disease.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>In the course of time, at the end of two years, his bowels came out because of the disease, and he died in great agony. His people made no fire in his honor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11644X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11644X\"></sup>like the fires made for his fathers.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11645Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11645Y\"></sup>He was thirty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem. And he departed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11645Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11645Z\"></sup>with no one's regret. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11645AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11645AA\"></sup>They buried him in the city of David, but not in the tombs of the kings."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11646A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11646A\"></sup>And the inhabitants of Jerusalem made Ahaziah, his youngest son, king in his place, for the band of men that came with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11646B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11646B\"></sup>the Arabians to the camp had killed all the older sons. So Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah reigned.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Ahaziah was twenty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Athaliah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11647C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11647C\"></sup>the granddaughter of Omri.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He also walked in the ways of the house of Ahab, for his mother was his counselor in doing wickedly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the house of Ahab had done. For after the death of his father they were his counselors, to his undoing.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He even followed their counsel and went with Jehoram the son of Ahab king of Israel to make war against Hazael king of Syria at Ramoth-gilead. And the Syrians wounded Joram,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and he returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds that he had received at Ramah, when he fought against Hazael king of Syria. And Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to see Joram the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was wounded.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But it was ordained by God that the downfall of Ahaziah should come about through his going to visit Joram. For when he came there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11652D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11652D\"></sup>he went out with Jehoram to meet Jehu the son of Nimshi, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11652E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11652E\"></sup>whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had anointed to destroy the house of Ahab.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11653F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11653F\"></sup>And when Jehu was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11653G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11653G\"></sup>executing judgment on the house of Ahab, he met the princes of Judah and the sons of Ahaziah's brothers, who attended Ahaziah, and he killed them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11654H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11654H\"></sup>He searched for Ahaziah, and he was captured while hiding in Samaria, and he was brought to Jehu and put to death. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11654I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11654I\"></sup>They buried him, for they said, “He is the grandson of Jehoshaphat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11654J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11654J\"></sup>who sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all his heart.” And the house of Ahaziah had no one able to rule the kingdom.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11655K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11655K\"></sup>Now when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she arose and destroyed all the royal family of the house of Judah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Jehoshabeath, the daughter of the king, took Joash the son of Ahaziah and stole him away from among the king's sons who were about to be put to death, and she put him and his nurse in a bedroom. Thus Jehoshabeath, the daughter of King Jehoram and wife of Jehoiada the priest, because she was a sister of Ahaziah, hid him from Athaliah, so that she did not put him to death.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he remained with them six years, hidden in the house of God, while Athaliah reigned over the land."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11658A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11658A\"></sup>But in the seventh year Jehoiada took courage and entered into a covenant with the commanders of hundreds, Azariah the son of Jeroham, Ishmael the son of Jehohanan, Azariah the son of Obed, Maaseiah the son of Adaiah, and Elishaphat the son of Zichri.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And they went about through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11659B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11659B\"></sup>Judah and gathered the Levites from all the cities of Judah, and the heads of fathers' houses of Israel, and they came to Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And all the assembly made a covenant with the king in the house of God. And Jehoiada said to them, “Behold, the king's son! Let him reign, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11660C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11660C\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke concerning the sons of David.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>This is the thing that you shall do: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11661D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11661D\"></sup>of you priests and Levites who come off duty on the Sabbath, one third shall be gatekeepers,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and one third shall be at the king's house and one third at the Gate of the Foundation. And all the people shall be in the courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Let no one enter the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> except the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11663E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11663E\"></sup>and ministering Levites. They may enter, for they are holy, but all the people shall keep the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Levites shall surround the king, each with his weapons in his hand. And whoever enters the house shall be put to death. Be with the king when he comes in and when he goes out.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Levites and all Judah did according to all that Jehoiada the priest commanded, and they each brought his men, who were to go off duty on the Sabbath, with those who were to come on duty on the Sabbath, for Jehoiada the priest did not dismiss <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11665F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11665F\"></sup>the divisions.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jehoiada the priest gave to the captains the spears and the large and small shields that had been King David's, which were in the house of God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he set all the people as a guard for the king, every man with his weapon in his hand, from the south side of the house to the north side of the house, around the altar and the house.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then they brought out the king's son and put the crown on him and gave him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11668G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11668G\"></sup>the testimony. And they proclaimed him king, and Jehoiada and his sons anointed him, and they said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11668H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11668H\"></sup>“Long live the king.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Athaliah heard the noise of the people running and praising the king, she went into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when she looked, there was the king standing by his pillar at the entrance, and the captains and the trumpeters beside the king, and all the people of the land rejoicing and blowing trumpets, and the singers with their musical instruments leading in the celebration. And Athaliah tore her clothes and cried, “Treason! Treason!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Jehoiada the priest brought out the captains who were set over the army, saying to them, “Bring her out between the ranks, and anyone who follows her is to be put to death with the sword.” For the priest said, “Do not put her to death in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they laid hands on her, and she went into the entrance of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11672I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11672I\"></sup>the horse gate of the king's house, and they put her to death there.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Jehoiada made a covenant between himself and all the people and the king that they should be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then all the people went to the house of Baal and tore it down; his altars and his images they broke in pieces, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11674J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11674J\"></sup>and they killed Mattan the priest of Baal before the altars.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Jehoiada posted watchmen for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> under the direction of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11675K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11675K\"></sup>the Levitical priests and the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11675L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11675L\"></sup>whom David had organized to be in charge of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to offer burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11675M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11675M\"></sup>as it is written in the Law of Moses, with rejoicing and with singing, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11675N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11675N\"></sup>according to the order of David.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He stationed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11676O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11676O\"></sup>the gatekeepers at the gates of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> so that no one should enter who was in any way unclean.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he took the captains, the nobles, the governors of the people, and all the people of the land, and they brought the king down from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, marching <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11677P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11677P\"></sup>through the upper gate to the king's house. And they set the king on the royal throne.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So all the people of the land rejoiced, and the city was quiet after Athaliah had been put to death with the sword."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11679A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11679A\"></sup>Joash was seven years old when he began to reign, and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Zibiah of Beersheba.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11680B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11680B\"></sup>And Joash did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the days of Jehoiada the priest.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jehoiada got for him two wives, and he had sons and daughters.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>After this Joash <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11682C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11682C\"></sup>decided to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11682D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11682D\"></sup>restore the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he gathered the priests and the Levites and said to them, “Go out to the cities of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11683E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11683E\"></sup>Judah and gather from all Israel money to repair the house of your God from year to year, and see that you act quickly.” But the Levites did not act quickly.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the king summoned Jehoiada the chief and said to him, “Why have you not required the Levites to bring in from Judah and Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11684F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11684F\"></sup>the tax levied by Moses, the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the congregation of Israel for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11684G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11684G\"></sup>the tent of testimony?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11685H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11685H\"></sup>the sons of Athaliah, that wicked woman, had broken into the house of God, and had also used all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11685I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11685I\"></sup>the dedicated things of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the Baals.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the king commanded, and they made a chest and set it outside the gate of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11687J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11687J\"></sup>proclamation was made throughout Judah and Jerusalem to bring in for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11687K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11687K\"></sup>the tax that Moses the servant of God laid on Israel in the wilderness.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And all the princes and all the people rejoiced and brought their tax and dropped it into the chest until they had finished.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And whenever the chest was brought to the king's officers by the Levites, when they saw that there was much money in it, the king's secretary and the officer of the chief priest would come and empty the chest and take it and return it to its place. Thus they did day after day, and collected money in abundance.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the king and Jehoiada gave it to those who had charge of the work of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they hired masons and carpenters to restore the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and also workers in iron and bronze to repair the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So those who were engaged in the work labored, and the repairing went forward in their hands, and they restored the house of God to its proper condition and strengthened it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And when they had finished, they brought the rest of the money before the king and Jehoiada, and with it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11692L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11692L\"></sup>were made utensils for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, both for the service and for the burnt offerings, and dishes for incense and vessels of gold and silver. And they offered burnt offerings in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regularly all the days of Jehoiada.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But Jehoiada grew old and full of days, and died. He was 130 years old at his death.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they buried him in the city of David among the kings, because he had done good in Israel, and toward God and his house.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now after the death of Jehoiada the princes of Judah came and paid homage to the king. Then the king listened to them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And they abandoned the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, and served <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11696M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11696M\"></sup>the Asherim and the idols. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11696N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11696N\"></sup>wrath came upon Judah and Jerusalem for this guilt of theirs.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11697O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11697O\"></sup>Yet he sent prophets among them to bring them back to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11697P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11697P\"></sup>These testified against them, but they would not pay attention.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11698Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11698Q\"></sup>Then the Spirit of God clothed Zechariah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11698R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11698R\"></sup>the son of Jehoiada the priest, and he stood above the people, and said to them, “Thus says God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11698S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11698S\"></sup>‘Why do you break the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so that you cannot prosper? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11698T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11698T\"></sup>Because you have forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he has forsaken you.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11699U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11699U\"></sup>they conspired against him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11699V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11699V\"></sup>and by command of the king they stoned him with stones in the court of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Thus Joash the king did not remember the kindness that Jehoiada, Zechariah's father, had shown him, but killed his son. And when he was dying, he said, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11700W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11700W\"></sup>and avenge!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>At the end of the year <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11701X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11701X\"></sup>the army of the Syrians came up against Joash. They came to Judah and Jerusalem and destroyed all the princes of the people from among the people and sent all their spoil to the king of Damascus.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Though the army of the Syrians had come with few men, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11702Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11702Y\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered into their hand a very great army, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11702Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11702Z\"></sup>because Judah had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers. Thus they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11702AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11702AA\"></sup>executed judgment on Joash.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When they had departed from him, leaving him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11703AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11703AB\"></sup>severely wounded, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11703AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11703AC\"></sup>his servants conspired against him because of the blood of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11703AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11703AD\"></sup>the son of Jehoiada the priest, and killed him on his bed. So he died, and they buried him in the city of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11703AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11703AE\"></sup>but they did not bury him in the tombs of the kings.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Those who conspired against him were Zabad the son of Shimeath the Ammonite, and Jehozabad the son of Shimrith the Moabite.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Accounts of his sons and of the many oracles against him and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11705AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11705AF\"></sup>the rebuilding of the house of God are written in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11705AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11705AG\"></sup>Story of the Book of the Kings. And Amaziah his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11706A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11706A\"></sup>Amaziah was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Jehoaddan of Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11707B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11707B\"></sup>yet not with a whole heart.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And as soon as the royal power was firmly his, he killed his servants who had struck down the king his father.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But he did not put their children to death, according to what is written in the Law, in the Book of Moses, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11709C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11709C\"></sup>“Fathers shall not die because of their children, nor children die because of their fathers, but each one shall die for his own sin.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Amaziah assembled the men of Judah and set them by fathers' houses under commanders of thousands and of hundreds for all Judah and Benjamin. He mustered those <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11710D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11710D\"></sup>twenty years old and upward, and found that they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11710E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11710E\"></sup>300,000 choice men, fit for war, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11710F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11710F\"></sup>able to handle spear and shield.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He hired also 100,000 mighty men of valor from Israel for 100 talents of silver.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11712G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11712G\"></sup>a man of God came to him and said, “O king, do not let the army of Israel go with you, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is not with Israel, with all these Ephraimites.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But go, act, be strong for the battle. Why should you suppose that God will cast you down before the enemy? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11713H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11713H\"></sup>For God has power to help or to cast down.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Amaziah said to the man of God, “But what shall we do about the hundred talents that I have given to the army of Israel?” The man of God answered, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is able to give you much more than this.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Amaziah discharged the army that had come to him from Ephraim to go home again. And they became very angry with Judah and returned home in fierce anger.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Amaziah took courage and led out his people and went to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11716I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11716I\"></sup>Valley of Salt and struck down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11716J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11716J\"></sup>10,000 men of Seir.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The men of Judah captured another 10,000 alive and took them to the top of a rock and threw them down from the top of the rock, and they were all dashed to pieces.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the men of the army whom Amaziah sent back, not letting them go with him to battle, raided the cities of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11718K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11718K\"></sup>from Samaria to Beth-horon, and struck down 3,000 people in them and took much spoil.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After Amaziah came from striking down the Edomites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11719L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11719L\"></sup>he brought the gods <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11719M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11719M\"></sup>of the men of Seir and set them up as his gods and worshiped them, making offerings to them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was angry with Amaziah and sent to him a prophet, who said to him, “Why have you sought the gods of a people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11720N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11720N\"></sup>who did not deliver their own people from your hand?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But as he was speaking, the king said to him, “Have we made you a royal counselor? Stop! Why should you be struck down?” So the prophet stopped, but said, “I know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11721O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11721O\"></sup>God has determined to destroy you, because you have done this and have not listened to my counsel.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11722P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11722P\"></sup>Then Amaziah king of Judah took counsel and sent to Joash the son of Jehoahaz, son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, “Come, let us look one another in the face.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Joash the king of Israel sent word to Amaziah king of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11723Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11723Q\"></sup>“A thistle on Lebanon sent to a cedar on Lebanon, saying, ‘Give your daughter to my son for a wife,’ and a wild beast of Lebanon passed by and trampled down the thistle.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You say, ‘See, I have struck down Edom,’ and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11724R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11724R\"></sup>your heart has lifted you up in boastfulness. But now stay at home. Why should you provoke trouble so that you fall, you and Judah with you?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But Amaziah would not listen, for it was of God, in order that he might give them into the hand of their enemies, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11725S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11725S\"></sup>because they had sought the gods of Edom.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Joash king of Israel went up, and he and Amaziah king of Judah faced one another in battle at Beth-shemesh, which belongs to Judah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Judah was defeated by Israel, and every man fled to his home.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Joash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Joash, son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11728T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11728T\"></sup>Ahaziah, at Beth-shemesh, and brought him to Jerusalem and broke down the wall of Jerusalem for 400 cubits, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11728U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11728U\"></sup>the Ephraim Gate to the Corner Gate.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he seized all the gold and silver, and all the vessels that were found in the house of God, in the care of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11729V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11729V\"></sup>Obed-edom. He seized also the treasuries of the king's house, also hostages, and he returned to Samaria.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11730W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11730W\"></sup>Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, lived fifteen years after the death of Joash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the rest of the deeds of Amaziah, from first to last, are they not written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>From the time when he turned away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they made a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to Lachish. But they sent after him to Lachish and put him to death there.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And they brought him upon horses, and he was buried with his fathers in the city of David."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>And all the people of Judah took Uzziah, who was sixteen years old, and made him king instead of his father Amaziah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He built Eloth and restored it to Judah, after the king slept with his fathers.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Uzziah was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11736A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11736A\"></sup>sixteen years old when he began to reign, and he reigned fifty-two years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Jecoliah of Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to all that his father Amaziah had done.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He set himself to seek God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11738B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11738B\"></sup>in the days of Zechariah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11738C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11738C\"></sup>who instructed him in the fear of God, and as long as he sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God made him prosper.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He went out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11739D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11739D\"></sup>made war against the Philistines and broke through the wall of Gath and the wall of Jabneh and the wall of Ashdod, and he built cities in the territory of Ashdod and elsewhere among the Philistines.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>God helped him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11740E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11740E\"></sup>against the Philistines and against the Arabians who lived in Gurbaal and against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11740F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11740F\"></sup>Meunites.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Ammonites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11741G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11741G\"></sup>paid tribute to Uzziah, and his fame spread even to the border of Egypt, for he became very strong.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Moreover, Uzziah built towers in Jerusalem at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11742H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11742H\"></sup>the Corner Gate and at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11742I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11742I\"></sup>the Valley Gate and at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11742J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11742J\"></sup>the Angle, and fortified them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he built towers in the wilderness and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11743K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11743K\"></sup>cut out many cisterns, for he had large herds, both in the Shephelah and in the plain, and he had farmers and vinedressers in the hills and in the fertile lands, for he loved the soil.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Moreover, Uzziah had an army of soldiers, fit for war, in divisions according to the numbers in the muster made by Jeiel the secretary and Maaseiah the officer, under the direction of Hananiah, one of the king's commanders.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The whole number of the heads of fathers' houses of mighty men of valor was 2,600.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Under their command was an army of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11746L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11746L\"></sup>307,500, who could make war with mighty power, to help the king against the enemy.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Uzziah prepared for all the army shields, spears, helmets, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11747M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11747M\"></sup>coats of mail, bows, and stones for slinging.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In Jerusalem he made machines, invented by skillful men, to be on the towers and the corners, to shoot arrows and great stones. And his fame spread far, for he was marvelously helped, till he was strong.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11749N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11749N\"></sup>he was strong, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11749O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11749O\"></sup>he grew proud, to his destruction. For he was unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God and entered the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to burn incense on the altar of incense.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11750P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11750P\"></sup>Azariah the priest went in after him, with eighty priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who were men of valor,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and they withstood King Uzziah and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11751Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11751Q\"></sup>“It is not for you, Uzziah, to burn incense to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11751R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11751R\"></sup>but for the priests, the sons of Aaron, who are consecrated to burn incense. Go out of the sanctuary, for you have done wrong, and it will bring you no honor from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Uzziah was angry. Now he had a censer in his hand to burn incense, and when he became angry with the priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11752S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11752S\"></sup>leprosy broke out on his forehead in the presence of the priests in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, by the altar of incense.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Azariah the chief priest and all the priests looked at him, and behold, he was leprous in his forehead! And they rushed him out quickly, and he himself hurried to go out, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had struck him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11754T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11754T\"></sup>And King Uzziah was a leper to the day of his death, and being a leper lived <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11754U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11754U\"></sup>in a separate house, for he was excluded from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And Jotham his son was over the king's household, governing the people of the land.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Uzziah, from first to last, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11755V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11755V\"></sup>Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz wrote.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Uzziah slept with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers in the burial field that belonged to the kings, for they said, “He is a leper.” And Jotham his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11757A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11757A\"></sup>Jotham was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Jerushah the daughter of Zadok.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> according to all that his father Uzziah had done, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11758B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11758B\"></sup>except he did not enter the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. But the people still followed corrupt practices.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He built the upper gate of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did much building on the wall of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11759C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11759C\"></sup>Ophel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moreover, he built cities in the hill country of Judah, and forts and towers on the wooded hills.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He fought with the king of the Ammonites and prevailed against them. And the Ammonites gave him that year 100 talents of silver, and 10,000 cors of wheat and 10,000 of barley. The Ammonites paid him the same amount in the second and the third years.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Jotham became mighty, because he ordered his ways before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11763D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11763D\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all his wars and his ways, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11764E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11764E\"></sup>twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jotham slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city of David, and Ahaz his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11766A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11766A\"></sup>Ahaz was twenty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. And he did not do what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as his father David had done,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>but he walked in the ways of the kings of Israel. He even made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11767B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11767B\"></sup>metal images for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11767C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11767C\"></sup>the Baals,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11768D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11768D\"></sup>he made offerings in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11768E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11768E\"></sup>Valley of the Son of Hinnom and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11768F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11768F\"></sup>burned his sons as an offering, according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11768G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11768G\"></sup>the abominations of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out before the people of Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he sacrificed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11769H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11769H\"></sup>made offerings on the high places and on the hills and under every green tree.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11770I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11770I\"></sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God gave him into the hand of the king of Syria, who defeated him and took captive a great number of his people and brought them to Damascus. He was also given into the hand of the king of Israel, who struck him with great force.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11771J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11771J\"></sup>Pekah the son of Remaliah killed 120,000 from Judah in one day, all of them men of valor, because they had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Zichri, a mighty man of Ephraim, killed Maaseiah the king's son and Azrikam the commander of the palace and Elkanah the next in authority to the king.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The men of Israel took captive 200,000 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11773K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11773K\"></sup>of their relatives, women, sons, and daughters. They also took much spoil from them and brought the spoil to Samaria.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was there, whose name was Oded, and he went out to meet the army that came to Samaria and said to them, “Behold, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11774L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11774L\"></sup>was angry with Judah, he gave them into your hand, but you have killed them in a rage <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11774M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11774M\"></sup>that has reached up to heaven.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And now you intend to subjugate the people of Judah and Jerusalem, male and female, as your slaves. Have you not sins of your own against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now hear me, and send back the captives <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11776N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11776N\"></sup>from your relatives whom you have taken, for the fierce wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is upon you.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Certain chiefs also of the men of Ephraim, Azariah the son of Johanan, Berechiah the son of Meshillemoth, Jehizkiah the son of Shallum, and Amasa the son of Hadlai, stood up against those who were coming from the war",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and said to them, “You shall not bring the captives in here, for you propose to bring upon us guilt against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in addition to our present sins and guilt. For our guilt is already great, and there is fierce wrath against Israel.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the armed men left the captives and the spoil before the princes and all the assembly.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11780O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11780O\"></sup>the men who have been mentioned by name rose and took the captives, and with the spoil they clothed all who were naked among them. They clothed them, gave them sandals, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11780P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11780P\"></sup>provided them with food and drink, and anointed them, and carrying all the feeble among them on donkeys, they brought them to their kinsfolk at Jericho, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11780Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11780Q\"></sup>the city of palm trees. Then they returned to Samaria.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11781R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11781R\"></sup>At that time King Ahaz sent to the king of Assyria for help.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For the Edomites had again invaded and defeated Judah and carried away captives.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11783S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11783S\"></sup>And the Philistines had made raids on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11783T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11783T\"></sup>the cities in the Shephelah and the Negeb of Judah, and had taken Beth-shemesh, Aijalon, Gederoth, Soco <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11783U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11783U\"></sup>with its villages, Timnah with its villages, and Gimzo with its villages. And they settled there.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> humbled Judah because of Ahaz king of Israel, for he had made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11784V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11784V\"></sup>Judah act sinfully and had been very unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11785W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11785W\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria came against him and afflicted him instead of strengthening him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11786X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11786X\"></sup>For Ahaz took a portion from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the house of the king and of the princes, and gave tribute to the king of Assyria, but it did not help him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>In the time of his distress he became yet more faithless to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—this same King Ahaz.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11788Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11788Y\"></sup>he sacrificed to the gods of Damascus that had defeated him and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11788Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11788Z\"></sup>“Because the gods of the kings of Syria helped them, I will sacrifice to them that they may help me.” But they were the ruin of him and of all Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Ahaz gathered together the vessels of the house of God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11789AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11789AA\"></sup>cut in pieces the vessels of the house of God, and he shut up the doors of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he made himself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11789AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11789AB\"></sup>altars in every corner of Jerusalem.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In every city of Judah he made high places to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11790AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11790AC\"></sup>make offerings to other gods, provoking to anger the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his fathers.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11791AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11791AD\"></sup>Now the rest of his acts and all his ways, from first to last, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Ahaz slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city, in Jerusalem, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11792AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11792AE\"></sup>they did not bring him into the tombs of the kings of Israel. And Hezekiah his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11793A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11793A\"></sup>Hezekiah began to reign when he was twenty-five years old, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Abijah the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11793B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11793B\"></sup>Zechariah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to all that David his father had done.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the first year of his reign, in the first month, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11795C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11795C\"></sup>opened the doors of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and repaired them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He brought in the priests and the Levites and assembled them in the square on the east",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and said to them, “Hear me, Levites! Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11797D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11797D\"></sup>consecrate yourselves, and consecrate the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, and carry out the filth from the Holy Place.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For our fathers have been unfaithful and have done what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God. They have forsaken him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11798E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11798E\"></sup>have turned away their faces from the habitation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and turned their backs.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11799F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11799F\"></sup>shut the doors of the vestibule and put out the lamps and have not burned incense or offered burnt offerings in the Holy Place to the God of Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11800G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11800G\"></sup>the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came on Judah and Jerusalem, and he has made them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11800H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11800H\"></sup>an object of horror, of astonishment, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11800I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11800I\"></sup>and of hissing, as you see with your own eyes.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11801J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11801J\"></sup>our fathers have fallen by the sword, and our sons and our daughters and our wives are in captivity for this.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11802K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11802K\"></sup>it is in my heart <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11802L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11802L\"></sup>to make a covenant with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, in order that his fierce anger may turn away from us.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My sons, do not now be negligent, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11803M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11803M\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen you to stand in his presence, to minister to him and to be his ministers and make offerings to him.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the Levites arose, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11804N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11804N\"></sup>Mahath the son of Amasai, and Joel the son of Azariah, of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11804O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11804O\"></sup>the Kohathites; and of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11804P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11804P\"></sup>Merari, Kish the son of Abdi, and Azariah the son of Jehallelel; and of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11804Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11804Q\"></sup>Gershonites, Joah the son of Zimmah, and Eden the son of Joah;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11805R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11805R\"></sup>Elizaphan, Shimri and Jeuel; and of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11805S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11805S\"></sup>Asaph, Zechariah and Mattaniah;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11806T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11806T\"></sup>Heman, Jehuel and Shimei; and of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11806U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11806U\"></sup>Jeduthun, Shemaiah and Uzziel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They gathered their brothers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11807V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11807V\"></sup>consecrated themselves and went in as the king had commanded, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11807W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11807W\"></sup>by the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11807X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11807X\"></sup>to cleanse the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The priests went into the inner part of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to cleanse it, and they brought out all the uncleanness that they found in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> into the court of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the Levites took it and carried it out to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11808Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11808Y\"></sup>the brook Kidron.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They began to consecrate <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11809Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11809Z\"></sup>on the first day of the first month, and on the eighth day of the month they came to the vestibule of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then for eight days they consecrated the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and on the sixteenth day of the first month they finished.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then they went in to Hezekiah the king and said, “We have cleansed all the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the altar of burnt offering and all its utensils, and the table for the showbread and all its utensils.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>All the utensils <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11811AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11811AA\"></sup>that King Ahaz discarded in his reign when he was faithless, we have made ready and consecrated, and behold, they are before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Hezekiah the king rose early and gathered the officials of the city and went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And they brought seven bulls, seven rams, seven lambs, and seven male goats <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11813AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11813AB\"></sup>for a sin offering for the kingdom and for the sanctuary and for Judah. And he commanded the priests, the sons of Aaron, to offer them on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they slaughtered the bulls, and the priests received the blood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11814AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11814AC\"></sup>and threw it against the altar. And they slaughtered the rams, and their blood was thrown against the altar. And they slaughtered the lambs, and their blood was thrown against the altar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the goats for the sin offering were brought to the king and the assembly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11815AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11815AD\"></sup>and they laid their hands on them,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and the priests slaughtered them and made a sin offering with their blood on the altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11816AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11816AE\"></sup>to make atonement for all Israel. For the king commanded that the burnt offering and the sin offering should be made for all Israel.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11817AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11817AF\"></sup>And he stationed the Levites in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with cymbals, harps, and lyres, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11817AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11817AG\"></sup>according to the commandment of David and of Gad <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11817AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11817AH\"></sup>the king's seer and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11817AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11817AI\"></sup>Nathan the prophet, for the commandment was from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through his prophets.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The Levites stood with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11818AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11818AJ\"></sup>the instruments of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11818AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11818AK\"></sup>and the priests with the trumpets.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then Hezekiah commanded that the burnt offering be offered on the altar. And when the burnt offering began, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11819AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11819AL\"></sup>the song to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began also, and the trumpets, accompanied by the instruments of David king of Israel.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The whole assembly worshiped, and the singers sang, and the trumpeters sounded. All this continued until the burnt offering was finished.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When the offering was finished, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11821AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11821AM\"></sup>the king and all who were present with him bowed themselves and worshiped.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Hezekiah the king and the officials commanded the Levites to sing praises to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the words of David and of Asaph the seer. And they sang praises with gladness, and they bowed down and worshiped.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Hezekiah said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11823AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11823AN\"></sup>“You have now consecrated yourselves to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Come near; bring sacrifices and thank offerings to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And the assembly brought sacrifices and thank offerings, and all who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11823AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11823AO\"></sup>of a willing heart brought burnt offerings.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The number of the burnt offerings that the assembly brought was 70 bulls, 100 rams, and 200 lambs; all these were for a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the consecrated offerings were 600 bulls and 3,000 sheep.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But the priests were too few and could not flay all the burnt offerings, so until other priests had consecrated themselves, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11826AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11826AP\"></sup>their brothers the Levites helped them, until the work was finished—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11826AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11826AQ\"></sup>for the Levites were more upright in heart than the priests in consecrating themselves.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Besides the great number of burnt offerings, there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11827AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11827AR\"></sup>the fat of the peace offerings, and there were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11827AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11827AS\"></sup>the drink offerings for the burnt offerings. Thus the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was restored.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And Hezekiah and all the people rejoiced because God had provided for the people, for the thing came about suddenly."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>Hezekiah sent to all Israel and Judah, and wrote letters also to Ephraim and Manasseh, that they should come to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Jerusalem to keep the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For the king and his princes and all the assembly in Jerusalem had taken counsel to keep the Passover <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11830A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11830A\"></sup>in the second month—",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>for they could not keep it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11831B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11831B\"></sup>at that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11831C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11831C\"></sup>because the priests had not consecrated themselves in sufficient number, nor had the people assembled in Jerusalem—",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and the plan seemed right to the king and all the assembly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So they decreed to make a proclamation throughout all Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11833D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11833D\"></sup>from Beersheba to Dan, that the people should come and keep the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, at Jerusalem, for they had not kept it as often as prescribed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11834E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11834E\"></sup>So couriers went throughout all Israel and Judah with letters from the king and his princes, as the king had commanded, saying, “O people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11834F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11834F\"></sup>return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, that he may turn again to the remnant of you who have escaped from the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11834G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11834G\"></sup>the kings of Assyria.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11835H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11835H\"></sup>Do not be like your fathers and your brothers, who were faithless to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of their fathers, so that he made them a desolation, as you see.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11836I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11836I\"></sup>Do not now be stiff-necked as your fathers were, but yield yourselves to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and come to his sanctuary, which he has consecrated forever, and serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11836J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11836J\"></sup>that his fierce anger may turn away from you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11837K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11837K\"></sup>if you return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, your brothers and your children <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11837L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11837L\"></sup>will find compassion with their captors and return to this land. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11837M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11837M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is gracious and merciful and will not turn away his face from you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11837N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11837N\"></sup>if you return to him.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11838O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11838O\"></sup>So the couriers went from city to city through the country of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11838P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11838P\"></sup>Ephraim and Manasseh, and as far as Zebulun, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11838Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11838Q\"></sup>they laughed them to scorn and mocked them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11839R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11839R\"></sup>some men of Asher, of Manasseh, and of Zebulun humbled themselves and came to Jerusalem.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The hand of God was also on Judah to give them one heart to do what the king and the princes commanded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11840S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11840S\"></sup>by the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And many people came together in Jerusalem to keep the Feast of Unleavened Bread <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11841T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11841T\"></sup>in the second month, a very great assembly.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They set to work and removed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11842U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11842U\"></sup>the altars that were in Jerusalem, and all the altars for burning incense they took away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11842V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11842V\"></sup>and threw into the brook Kidron.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11843W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11843W\"></sup>And they slaughtered the Passover lamb on the fourteenth day of the second month. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11843X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11843X\"></sup>And the priests and the Levites were ashamed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11843Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11843Y\"></sup>so that they consecrated themselves and brought burnt offerings into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11844Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11844Z\"></sup>They took their accustomed posts according to the Law of Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11844AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11844AA\"></sup>the man of God. The priests threw the blood that they received from the hand of the Levites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For there were many in the assembly who had not consecrated themselves. Therefore the Levites had to slaughter the Passover lamb for everyone who was not clean, to consecrate it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For a majority of the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11846AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11846AB\"></sup>many of them from Ephraim, Manasseh, Issachar, and Zebulun, had not cleansed themselves, yet they ate the Passover otherwise <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11846AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11846AC\"></sup>than as prescribed. For Hezekiah had prayed for them, saying, “May the good <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pardon everyone",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11847AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11847AD\"></sup>who sets his heart to seek God, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his fathers, even though not according to the sanctuary's rules of cleanness.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard Hezekiah and healed the people.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the people of Israel who were present at Jerusalem kept <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11849AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11849AE\"></sup>the Feast of Unleavened Bread seven days with great gladness, and the Levites and the priests praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> day by day, singing with all their might to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Hezekiah spoke <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11850AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11850AF\"></sup>encouragingly to all the Levites who showed good skill in the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. So they ate the food of the festival for seven days, sacrificing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11850AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11850AG\"></sup>peace offerings and giving thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the whole assembly agreed together to keep the feast <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11851AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11851AH\"></sup>for another seven days. So they kept it for another seven days with gladness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For Hezekiah king of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11852AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11852AI\"></sup>gave the assembly 1,000 bulls and 7,000 sheep for offerings, and the princes gave the assembly 1,000 bulls and 10,000 sheep. And the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11852AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11852AJ\"></sup>consecrated themselves in great numbers.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The whole assembly of Judah, and the priests and the Levites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11853AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11853AK\"></sup>and the whole assembly that came out of Israel, and the sojourners who came out of the land of Israel, and the sojourners who lived in Judah, rejoiced.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So there was great joy in Jerusalem, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11854AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11854AL\"></sup>since the time of Solomon the son of David king of Israel there had been nothing like this in Jerusalem.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11855AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11855AM\"></sup>the priests and the Levites arose and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11855AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11855AN\"></sup>blessed the people, and their voice was heard, and their prayer came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11855AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11855AO\"></sup>his holy habitation in heaven."
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>Now when all this was finished, all Israel who were present went out to the cities of Judah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11856A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11856A\"></sup>broke in pieces the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11856B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11856B\"></sup>pillars and cut down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11856C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11856C\"></sup>the Asherim and broke down the high places and the altars throughout all Judah and Benjamin, and in Ephraim and Manasseh, until they had destroyed them all. Then all the people of Israel returned to their cities, every man to his possession.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Hezekiah appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11857D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11857D\"></sup>the divisions of the priests and of the Levites, division by division, each according to his service, the priests and the Levites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11857E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11857E\"></sup>for burnt offerings and peace offerings, to minister in the gates of the camp of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to give thanks and praise.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11858F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11858F\"></sup>The contribution of the king from his own possessions was for the burnt offerings: the burnt offerings of morning and evening, and the burnt offerings for the Sabbaths, the new moons, and the appointed feasts, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11858G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11858G\"></sup>as it is written in the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he commanded the people who lived in Jerusalem to give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11859H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11859H\"></sup>the portion due to the priests and the Levites, that they might give themselves to the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As soon as the command was spread abroad, the people of Israel gave in abundance the firstfruits of grain, wine, oil, honey, and of all the produce of the field. And they brought in abundantly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11860I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11860I\"></sup>the tithe of everything.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the people of Israel and Judah who lived in the cities of Judah also brought in the tithe of cattle and sheep, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11861J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11861J\"></sup>the tithe of the dedicated things that had been dedicated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, and laid them in heaps.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In the third month they began to pile up the heaps, and finished them in the seventh month.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Hezekiah and the princes came and saw the heaps, they blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his people Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Hezekiah questioned the priests and the Levites about the heaps.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Azariah the chief priest, who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11865K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11865K\"></sup>of the house of Zadok, answered him, “Since they began to bring the contributions into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, we have eaten and had enough and have plenty left, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11865L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11865L\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed his people, so that we have this large amount left.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Hezekiah commanded them to prepare <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11866M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11866M\"></sup>chambers in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they prepared them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they faithfully brought in the contributions, the tithes, and the dedicated things. The chief officer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11867N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11867N\"></sup>in charge of them was Conaniah the Levite, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11867O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11867O\"></sup>Shimei his brother as second,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11868P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11868P\"></sup>while Jehiel, Azaziah, Nahath, Asahel, Jerimoth, Jozabad, Eliel, Ismachiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11868Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11868Q\"></sup>Mahath, and Benaiah were overseers assisting Conaniah and Shimei his brother, by the appointment of Hezekiah the king and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11868R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11868R\"></sup>Azariah the chief officer of the house of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Kore the son of Imnah the Levite, keeper of the east gate, was over the freewill offerings to God, to apportion the contribution reserved for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the most holy offerings.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11870S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11870S\"></sup>Eden, Miniamin, Jeshua, Shemaiah, Amariah, and Shecaniah were faithfully assisting him in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11870T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11870T\"></sup>the cities of the priests, to distribute the portions to their brothers, old and young alike, by divisions,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>except those enrolled by genealogy, males from three years old and upward—all who entered the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11871U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11871U\"></sup>as the duty of each day required—for their service according to their offices, by their divisions.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The enrollment of the priests was according to their fathers' houses; that of the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11872V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11872V\"></sup>from twenty years old and upward was according to their offices, by their divisions.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They were enrolled with all their little children, their wives, their sons, and their daughters, the whole assembly, for they were faithful in keeping themselves holy.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And for the sons of Aaron, the priests, who were in the fields of common land belonging to their cities, there were men in the several cities who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11874W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11874W\"></sup>designated by name to distribute portions to every male among the priests and to everyone among the Levites who was enrolled.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Thus Hezekiah did throughout all Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11875X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11875X\"></sup>and he did what was good and right and faithful before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And every work that he undertook in the service of the house of God and in accordance with the law and the commandments, seeking his God, he did with all his heart, and prospered."
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11877A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11877A\"></sup>After these things and these acts of faithfulness, Sennacherib king of Assyria came and invaded Judah and encamped against the fortified cities, thinking to win them for himself.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And when Hezekiah saw that Sennacherib had come and intended to fight against Jerusalem,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>he planned with his officers and his mighty men to stop the water of the springs that were outside the city; and they helped him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>A great many people were gathered, and they stopped all the springs and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11880B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11880B\"></sup>the brook that flowed through the land, saying, “Why should the kings of Assyria come and find much water?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He set to work resolutely and built up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11881C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11881C\"></sup>all the wall that was broken down and raised towers upon it, and outside it he built another wall, and he strengthened the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11881D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11881D\"></sup>Millo in the city of David. He also made weapons and shields in abundance.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he set combat commanders over the people and gathered them together to him in the square at the gate of the city and spoke <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11882E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11882E\"></sup>encouragingly to them, saying,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11883F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11883F\"></sup>“Be strong and courageous. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11883G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11883G\"></sup>Do not be afraid or dismayed before the king of Assyria and all the horde that is with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11883H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11883H\"></sup>for there are more with us than with him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>With him is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11884I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11884I\"></sup>an arm of flesh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11884J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11884J\"></sup>but with us is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, to help us and to fight our battles.” And the people took confidence from the words of Hezekiah king of Judah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After this, Sennacherib king of Assyria, who was besieging Lachish with all his forces, sent his servants to Jerusalem to Hezekiah king of Judah and to all the people of Judah who were in Jerusalem, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Thus says Sennacherib king of Assyria, ‘On what are you trusting, that you endure the siege in Jerusalem?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Is not Hezekiah misleading you, that he may give you over to die by famine and by thirst, when he tells you, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God will deliver us from the hand of the king of Assyria”?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11888K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11888K\"></sup>Has not this same Hezekiah taken away his high places and his altars and commanded Judah and Jerusalem, “Before one altar you shall worship, and on it you shall burn your sacrifices”?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Do you not know what I and my fathers have done to all the peoples of other lands? Were the gods of the nations of those lands at all able to deliver their lands out of my hand?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Who among all the gods of those nations that my fathers devoted to destruction was able to deliver his people from my hand, that your God should be able to deliver you from my hand?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now, therefore, do not let Hezekiah deceive you or mislead you in this fashion, and do not believe him, for no god of any nation or kingdom has been able to deliver his people from my hand or from the hand of my fathers. How much less will your God deliver you out of my hand!’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And his servants said still more against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God and against his servant Hezekiah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he wrote letters to cast contempt on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, and to speak against him, saying, “Like the gods of the nations of the lands who have not delivered their people from my hands, so the God of Hezekiah will not deliver his people from my hand.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And they shouted it with a loud voice in the language of Judah to the people of Jerusalem who were on the wall, to frighten and terrify them, in order that they might take the city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And they spoke of the God of Jerusalem as they spoke of the gods of the peoples of the earth, which are the work of men's hands.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Hezekiah the king and Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, prayed because of this and cried to heaven.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent an angel, who cut off all the mighty warriors and commanders and officers in the camp of the king of Assyria. So he returned with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11897L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11897L\"></sup>shame of face to his own land. And when he came into the house of his god, some of his own sons struck him down there with the sword.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saved Hezekiah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem from the hand of Sennacherib king of Assyria and from the hand of all his enemies, and he provided for them on every side.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And many <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11899M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11899M\"></sup>brought gifts to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to Jerusalem and precious things to Hezekiah king of Judah, so that he was exalted in the sight of all nations from that time onward.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11900N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11900N\"></sup>In those days Hezekiah became sick and was at the point of death, and he prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he answered him and gave him a sign.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Hezekiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11901O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11901O\"></sup>did not make return according to the benefit done to him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11901P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11901P\"></sup>his heart was proud. Therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11901Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11901Q\"></sup>wrath came upon him and Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Hezekiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11902R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11902R\"></sup>humbled himself for the pride of his heart, both he and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not come upon them in the days of Hezekiah.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Hezekiah had very great riches and honor, and he made for himself treasuries for silver, for gold, for precious stones, for spices, for shields, and for all kinds of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11903S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11903S\"></sup>costly vessels;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>storehouses also for the yield of grain, wine, and oil; and stalls for all kinds of cattle, and sheepfolds.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He likewise provided cities for himself, and flocks and herds in abundance, for God had given him very great possessions.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>This same Hezekiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11906T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11906T\"></sup>closed the upper outlet of the waters of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11906U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11906U\"></sup>Gihon and directed them down to the west side of the city of David. And Hezekiah prospered in all his works.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And so in the matter of the envoys of the princes of Babylon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11907V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11907V\"></sup>who had been sent to him to inquire about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11907W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11907W\"></sup>the sign that had been done in the land, God left him to himself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11907X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11907X\"></sup>in order to test him and to know all that was in his heart.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah and his good deeds, behold, they are written <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11908Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11908Y\"></sup>in the vision of Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11908Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11908Z\"></sup>in the Book of the Kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And Hezekiah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11909AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11909AA\"></sup>upper part of the tombs of the sons of David, and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem did him honor at his death. And Manasseh his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11910A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11910A\"></sup>Manasseh was twelve years old when he began to reign, and he reigned fifty-five years in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11911B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11911B\"></sup>the abominations of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out before the people of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For he rebuilt the high places <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11912C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11912C\"></sup>that his father Hezekiah had broken down, and he erected altars to the Baals, and made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11912D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11912D\"></sup>Asheroth, and worshiped all the host of heaven and served them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he built altars in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11913E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11913E\"></sup>“In Jerusalem shall my name be forever.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he built altars for all the host of heaven in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11914F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11914F\"></sup>the two courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11915G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11915G\"></sup>And he burned his sons as an offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11915H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11915H\"></sup>in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11915I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11915I\"></sup>used fortune-telling and omens and sorcery, and dealt with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11915J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11915J\"></sup>mediums and with necromancers. He did much evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, provoking him to anger.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11916K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11916K\"></sup>the carved image of the idol that he had made he set in the house of God, of which God said to David and to Solomon his son, “In this house, and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11916L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11916L\"></sup>I will put my name forever,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and I will no more remove the foot of Israel from the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11917M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11917M\"></sup>that I appointed for your fathers, if only they will be careful to do all that I have commanded them, all the law, the statutes, and the rules given through Moses.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Manasseh led Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem astray, to do more evil than the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroyed before the people of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Manasseh and to his people, but they paid no attention.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11920N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11920N\"></sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought upon them the commanders of the army of the king of Assyria, who captured Manasseh with hooks and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11920O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11920O\"></sup>bound him with chains of bronze and brought him to Babylon.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And when he was in distress, he entreated the favor of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11921P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11921P\"></sup>and humbled himself greatly before the God of his fathers.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He prayed to him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11922Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11922Q\"></sup>God was moved by his entreaty and heard his plea and brought him again to Jerusalem into his kingdom. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11922R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11922R\"></sup>Then Manasseh knew that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Afterward he built an outer wall for the city of David west of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11923S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11923S\"></sup>Gihon, in the valley, and for the entrance into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11923T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11923T\"></sup>the Fish Gate, and carried it around <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11923U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11923U\"></sup>Ophel, and raised it to a very great height. He also put commanders of the army in all the fortified cities in Judah.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11924V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11924V\"></sup>he took away the foreign gods and the idol from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and all the altars that he had built on the mountain of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in Jerusalem, and he threw them outside of the city.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He also restored the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and offered on it sacrifices of peace offerings and of thanksgiving, and he commanded Judah to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11926W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11926W\"></sup>Nevertheless, the people still sacrificed at the high places, but only to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11927X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11927X\"></sup>his prayer to his God, and the words of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11927Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11927Y\"></sup>the seers who spoke to him in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, behold, they are in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11927Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11927Z\"></sup>Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And his prayer, and how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11928AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11928AA\"></sup>God was moved by his entreaty, and all his sin and his faithlessness, and the sites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11928AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11928AB\"></sup>on which he built high places and set up the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11928AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11928AC\"></sup>Asherim and the images, before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11928AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11928AD\"></sup>he humbled himself, behold, they are written in the Chronicles of the Seers.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Manasseh slept with his fathers, and they buried him in his house, and Amon his son reigned in his place.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11930AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11930AE\"></sup>Amon was twenty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned two years in Jerusalem.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as Manasseh his father had done. Amon sacrificed to all the images <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11931AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11931AF\"></sup>that Manasseh his father had made, and served them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he did not humble himself before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11932AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11932AG\"></sup>as Manasseh his father had humbled himself, but this Amon incurred guilt more and more.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And his servants conspired against him and put him to death in his house.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But the people of the land struck down all those who had conspired against King Amon. And the people of the land made Josiah his son king in his place."
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11935A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11935A\"></sup>Josiah was eight years old when he began to reign, and he reigned thirty-one years in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and walked in the ways of David his father; and he did not turn aside to the right hand or to the left.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For in the eighth year of his reign, while he was yet a boy, he began to seek the God of David his father, and in the twelfth year he began to purge Judah and Jerusalem of the high places, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11937B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11937B\"></sup>Asherim, and the carved and the metal images.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And they chopped down the altars of the Baals in his presence, and he cut down the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11938C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11938C\"></sup>incense altars that stood above them. And he broke in pieces the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11938D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11938D\"></sup>Asherim and the carved and the metal images, and he made dust of them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11938E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11938E\"></sup>scattered it over the graves of those who had sacrificed to them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11939F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11939F\"></sup>He also burned the bones of the priests on their altars and cleansed Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11940G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11940G\"></sup>cities of Manasseh, Ephraim, and Simeon, and as far as Naphtali, in their ruins all around,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>he broke down the altars and beat the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11941H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11941H\"></sup>Asherim and the images <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11941I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11941I\"></sup>into powder and cut down all the incense altars throughout all the land of Israel. Then he returned to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11942J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11942J\"></sup>Now in the eighteenth year of his reign, when he had cleansed the land and the house, he sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah, and Maaseiah the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11942K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11942K\"></sup>governor of the city, and Joah the son of Joahaz, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11942L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11942L\"></sup>the recorder, to repair the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11943M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11943M\"></sup>Hilkiah the high priest and gave him the money that had been brought into the house of God, which the Levites, the keepers of the threshold, had collected from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11943N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11943N\"></sup>Manasseh and Ephraim and from all the remnant of Israel and from all Judah and Benjamin and from the inhabitants of Jerusalem.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And they gave it to the workmen who were working in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the workmen who were working in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave it for repairing and restoring the house.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They gave it to the carpenters and the builders to buy quarried stone, and timber for binders and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11945O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11945O\"></sup>beams for the buildings that the kings of Judah had let go to ruin.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the men did the work faithfully. Over them were set Jahath and Obadiah the Levites, of the sons of Merari, and Zechariah and Meshullam, of the sons of the Kohathites, to have oversight. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11946P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11946P\"></sup>The Levites, all who were skillful with instruments of music,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>were over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11947Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11947Q\"></sup>the burden-bearers and directed all who did work in every kind of service, and some of the Levites were scribes and officials and gatekeepers.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>While they were bringing out the money that had been brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11948R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11948R\"></sup>Hilkiah the priest found the Book of the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> given through Moses.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Hilkiah answered and said to Shaphan the secretary, “I have found the Book of the Law in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And Hilkiah gave the book to Shaphan.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Shaphan brought the book to the king, and further reported to the king, “All that was committed to your servants they are doing.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They have emptied out the money that was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and have given it into the hand of the overseers and the workmen.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Shaphan the secretary told the king, “Hilkiah the priest has given me a book.” And Shaphan read from it before the king.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And when the king heard the words of the Law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11953S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11953S\"></sup>he tore his clothes.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the king commanded Hilkiah, Ahikam the son of Shaphan, Abdon the son of Micah, Shaphan the secretary, and Asaiah the king's servant, saying,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Go, inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for me and for those who are left in Israel and in Judah, concerning the words of the book that has been found. For great is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11955T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11955T\"></sup>the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that is poured out on us, because our fathers have not kept the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to do according to all that is written in this book.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Hilkiah and those whom the king had sent went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tokhath, son of Hasrah, keeper of the wardrobe (now she lived in Jerusalem in the Second Quarter) and spoke to her to that effect.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And she said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: ‘Tell the man who sent you to me,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Behold, I will bring disaster upon this place and upon its inhabitants, all the curses that are written in the book that was read before the king of Judah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Because they have forsaken me and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11959U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11959U\"></sup>have made offerings to other gods, that they might provoke me to anger with all the works of their hands, therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11959V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11959V\"></sup>my wrath will be poured out on this place and will not be quenched.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But to the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, thus shall you say to him, Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: Regarding the words that you have heard,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>because your heart was tender and you humbled yourself before God when you heard his words against this place and its inhabitants, and you have humbled yourself before me and have torn your clothes and wept before me, I also have heard you, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Behold, I will gather you to your fathers, and you shall be gathered to your grave in peace, and your eyes shall not see all the disaster that I will bring upon this place and its inhabitants.’” And they brought back word to the king.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11963W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11963W\"></sup>Then the king sent and gathered together all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the king went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with all the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem and the priests and the Levites, all the people both great and small. And he read in their hearing all the words of the Book of the Covenant that had been found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11965X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11965X\"></sup>stood in his place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11965Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11965Y\"></sup>and made a covenant before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to walk after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to keep his commandments and his testimonies and his statutes, with all his heart and all his soul, to perform the words of the covenant that were written in this book.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then he made all who were present in Jerusalem and in Benjamin join in it. And the inhabitants of Jerusalem did according to the covenant of God, the God of their fathers.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And Josiah took away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11967Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11967Z\"></sup>all the abominations from all the territory that belonged to the people of Israel and made all who were present in Israel serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God. All his days they did not turn away from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers."
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11968A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11968A\"></sup>Josiah kept a Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem. And they slaughtered the Passover lamb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11968B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11968B\"></sup>on the fourteenth day of the first month.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He appointed the priests to their offices <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11969C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11969C\"></sup>and encouraged them in the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he said to the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11970D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11970D\"></sup>who taught all Israel and who were holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Put the holy ark in the house that Solomon the son of David, king of Israel, built. You need not carry it on your shoulders. Now serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and his people Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Prepare yourselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11971E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11971E\"></sup>according to your fathers' houses by your divisions, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11971F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11971F\"></sup>as prescribed in the writing of David king of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11971G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11971G\"></sup>and the document of Solomon his son.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11972H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11972H\"></sup>stand in the Holy Place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11972I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11972I\"></sup>according to the groupings of the fathers' houses of your brothers the lay people, and according to the division of the Levites by fathers' household.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And slaughter the Passover lamb, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11973J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11973J\"></sup>consecrate yourselves, and prepare for your brothers, to do according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by Moses.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Josiah contributed to the lay people, as Passover offerings for all who were present, lambs and young goats from the flock to the number of 30,000, and 3,000 bulls; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11974K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11974K\"></sup>these were from the king's possessions.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And his officials contributed willingly to the people, to the priests, and to the Levites. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11975L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11975L\"></sup>Hilkiah, Zechariah, and Jehiel, the chief officers of the house of God, gave to the priests for the Passover offerings 2,600 Passover lambs and 300 bulls.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Conaniah also, and Shemaiah and Nethanel his brothers, and Hashabiah and Jeiel and Jozabad, the chiefs of the Levites, gave to the Levites for the Passover offerings 5,000 lambs and young goats and 500 bulls.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When the service had been prepared for, the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11977M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11977M\"></sup>stood in their place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11977N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11977N\"></sup>and the Levites in their divisions according to the king's command.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11978O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11978O\"></sup>And they slaughtered the Passover lamb, and the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11978P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11978P\"></sup>threw the blood that they received from them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11978Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11978Q\"></sup>while the Levites flayed the sacrifices.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they set aside the burnt offerings that they might distribute them according to the groupings of the fathers' houses of the lay people, to offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as it is written in the Book of Moses. And so they did with the bulls.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11980R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11980R\"></sup>And they roasted the Passover lamb with fire according to the rule; and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11980S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11980S\"></sup>boiled the holy offerings in pots, in cauldrons, and in pans, and carried them quickly to all the lay people.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And afterward they prepared for themselves and for the priests, because the priests, the sons of Aaron, were offering the burnt offerings and the fat parts until night; so the Levites prepared for themselves and for the priests, the sons of Aaron.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The singers, the sons of Asaph, were in their place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11982T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11982T\"></sup>according to the command of David, and Asaph, and Heman, and Jeduthun the king's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11982U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11982U\"></sup>seer; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11982V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11982V\"></sup>and the gatekeepers were at each gate. They did not need to depart from their service, for their brothers the Levites prepared for them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So all the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was prepared that day, to keep the Passover and to offer burnt offerings on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to the command of King Josiah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the people of Israel who were present kept the Passover at that time, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11984W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11984W\"></sup>and the Feast of Unleavened Bread seven days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11985X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11985X\"></sup>No Passover like it had been kept in Israel since the days of Samuel the prophet. None of the kings of Israel had kept such a Passover as was kept by Josiah, and the priests and the Levites, and all Judah and Israel who were present, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>In the eighteenth year of the reign of Josiah this Passover was kept.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11987Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11987Y\"></sup>After all this, when Josiah had prepared the temple, Neco king of Egypt went up to fight at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11987Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11987Z\"></sup>Carchemish on the Euphrates, and Josiah went out to meet him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But he sent envoys to him, saying, “What have we to do with each other, king of Judah? I am not coming against you this day, but against the house with which I am at war. And God has commanded me to hurry. Cease opposing God, who is with me, lest he destroy you.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Nevertheless, Josiah did not turn away from him, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11989AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11989AA\"></sup>disguised himself in order to fight with him. He did not listen to the words of Neco from the mouth of God, but came to fight in the plain of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11989AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11989AB\"></sup>Megiddo.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the archers shot King Josiah. And the king said to his servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11990AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11990AC\"></sup>“Take me away, for I am badly wounded.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So his servants took him out of the chariot and carried him in his second chariot and brought him to Jerusalem. And he died and was buried in the tombs of his fathers. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11991AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11991AD\"></sup>All Judah and Jerusalem mourned for Josiah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11992AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11992AE\"></sup>Jeremiah also uttered a lament for Josiah; and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11992AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11992AF\"></sup>the singing men and singing women have spoken of Josiah in their laments to this day. They made these a rule in Israel; behold, they are written in the Laments.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Josiah, and his good deeds according to what is written in the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and his acts, first and last, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah."
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">36 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11995A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11995A\"></sup>The people of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah and made him king in his father's place in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he began to reign, and he reigned three months in Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king of Egypt deposed him in Jerusalem and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11997B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11997B\"></sup>laid on the land a tribute of a hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the king of Egypt made Eliakim his brother king over Judah and Jerusalem, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. But Neco took Jehoahaz his brother and carried him to Egypt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11999C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11999C\"></sup>Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12000D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12000D\"></sup>Against him came up Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12000E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12000E\"></sup>and bound him in chains <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12000F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12000F\"></sup>to take him to Babylon.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12001G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12001G\"></sup>Nebuchadnezzar also carried part of the vessels of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to Babylon and put them in his palace in Babylon.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12002H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12002H\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, and the abominations that he did, and what was found against him, behold, they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and Judah. And Jehoiachin his son reigned in his place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12003I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12003I\"></sup>Jehoiachin was eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned three months and ten days in Jerusalem. He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12004J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12004J\"></sup>the spring of the year King Nebuchadnezzar sent and brought him to Babylon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12004K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12004K\"></sup>with the precious vessels of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and made his brother <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12004L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12004L\"></sup>Zedekiah king over Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12005M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12005M\"></sup>Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God. He did not humble himself before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12006N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12006N\"></sup>Jeremiah the prophet, who spoke from the mouth of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12007O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12007O\"></sup>He also rebelled against King Nebuchadnezzar, who had made him swear by God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12007P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12007P\"></sup>He stiffened his neck and hardened his heart against turning to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>All the officers of the priests and the people likewise were exceedingly unfaithful, following all the abominations of the nations. And they polluted the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he had made holy in Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12009Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12009Q\"></sup>sent persistently to them by his messengers, because he had compassion on his people and on his dwelling place.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12010R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12010R\"></sup>But they kept mocking the messengers of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12010S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12010S\"></sup>despising his words and scoffing at his prophets, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12010T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12010T\"></sup>until the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rose against his people, until there was no remedy.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12011U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12011U\"></sup>Therefore he brought up against them the king of the Chaldeans, who killed their young men with the sword in the house of their sanctuary and had no compassion on young man or virgin, old man or aged. He gave them all into his hand.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12012V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12012V\"></sup>And all the vessels of the house of God, great and small, and the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the treasures of the king and of his princes, all these he brought to Babylon.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12013W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12013W\"></sup>And they burned the house of God and broke down the wall of Jerusalem and burned all its palaces with fire and destroyed all its precious vessels.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12014X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12014X\"></sup>took into exile in Babylon those who had escaped from the sword, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12014Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12014Y\"></sup>and they became servants to him and to his sons until the establishment of the kingdom of Persia,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>to fulfill the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by the mouth of Jeremiah, until the land had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12015Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12015Z\"></sup>enjoyed its Sabbaths. All the days that it lay desolate <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12015AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12015AA\"></sup>it kept Sabbath, to fulfill seventy years.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12016AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12016AB\"></sup>Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12016AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12016AC\"></sup>that the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by the mouth of Jeremiah might be fulfilled, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12016AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12016AD\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stirred up the spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, so that he made a proclamation throughout all his kingdom and also put it in writing:",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Thus says Cyrus king of Persia, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven, has given me all the kingdoms of the earth, and he has charged me to build him a house at Jerusalem, which is in Judah. Whoever is among you of all his people, may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God be with him. Let him go up.’”"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;